text:
the violence against women's act (vawa) also allowed for undocumented survivors to be able to come forward and make reports without fear of deportation. 
vawa crosses across many movements. women need wava, undocumented survivors need vawa, trans survivors need vawa, children need vawa, male survivors also need vawa.

allowing wava to expires sends a clear message - the same message this administration has sent since its campaign, fueled by elected representatives with the same agenda. that message is we don't matter. .
.

text:
i support people's decision to be themselves, even if i don't agree with it. as long as what you're doing isn't harming anyone in anyway i see no need to offer my three cent. too often i think people spend their time focused on the wrong people, places, and or things. just be yourself, and if possible, express yourself while also encouraging someone else to do the same. be happy. love yourself. love others. if all else fails--just mind your own damn business. have a great life everyone.

text:
🌈
ما حامی ترنسها هستیم نه ترتس نماها !!
سوال پیش میاد کی به حمایت شما‌ها نیاز داره ؟!
‏این زمان و هزینه رو صرف ساختن همچین برنامه‌های مسخره‌ای میکنید، خودتون که مسخره هستید، یک عده آدم بیسواد و ناآگاه رو هم میارید جلوی دوربین که حماقت خودشون رو اثبات کنن!!
بهتون توصیه می‌کنم که دست در شورت راه برید که ‎#مردانگیتون رو گم نکنید...
.
‌از نظر این نرسانان و ماده سانان هر کسی خارج از نُرم زنانگی و مردانگیشون باشه ترنس نما هست توی ویدئو تعدادیشون که تو اینستا فعالن هم هست، به طور کلی هر کوئیری که عقیم سازی اجباری رو انجام نده و مرد و زن مشخصی که اینا میخوان نباشه :|
.
‏این دقیقا کف جامعه است
جامعه‌ای که مردونگی و زنونگی رو از کتاب عربی یاد گرفته!
مردی که مردونگی رو به کمربند کشیدن میدونه
زنی که مردونگی رو به تملک میدونه (سوئیچ)
.
‌شک ندارم خیلی از خود ترنس‌ها هم از این ویدئو خوشحال میشن چون همون افکار پوسیده رو دارن و همونجور دگم هستند
#فرهنگ_منفی #ترنس #ترنسجندر #ترنسکشوال #مردانگی #زنانگی
#lgbt #metoo #trans #transgender

text:
[kilas balik 16 film festival bali 2018]

1 desember 2018.

opening night diadakan di uma seminyak (@umaseminyak) pukul 17:00 wita. ada beberapa kegiatan yang dilakukan pada hari tersebut, yaitu pemutaran film, sesi #hearmetoo dan penampilan puisi visual.

kegiatan diawali dengan pemutaran film "posesif" (2017) karya edwin. kemudian dilanjutkan dengan #hearmetoo session dengan tema "kekerasan dalam pacaran dari sisi kesehatan mental dan hukum" bersama @candramertha (pengacara publik ylbhi-lbh bali), @dokteraidotcom dan penyintas kekerasan dalam pacaran. kegiatan ditutup dengan penampilan puisi visual oleh @liberal.literasi dengan judul "si puan".
.
@gshrudayana @kisara_bali @lbh_bali

#gshrudayana #genderstudies #sexualitystudies #humanrightsstudies #bali #hearmetoo #metoo #gerakbersama #hapuskekerasanseksual #enambelasffest #enambelasffestbali

text: being a woman in northeastern nc is being a 2nd class citizen. there was barely a civil rights movement here and no women’s movement ever. organized religion and societal expectations serve to keep women silent and in their places. even professional, educated ones. today i was asked to collaborate on a film about rural women in eastern nc. finally! humbled and so very thankful. photo credit f. roy johnson. 1940s. #ahoskienc #hertfordcountync #rural #women #womenofcolor #easternnc #intersectionalfeminism #womanism #metoo

text:
2018 ha sido un año que me ha roto los esquemas (quizá) más de lo que merecía. joder, ahora que lo recuerdo, ha sido un puta montaña rusa de emociones. “nunca digas nunca”, debería estar tatuado en mi piel, porque he roto todas las promesas que un día me hice a mí misma. he salido de la jaula, me he sentido más libre que nunca, he hecho cosas que jamás hubiera imaginado que me atrevería a hacer... y no me arrepiento de nada.

el 2018 no me ha puesto las cosas fáciles, pero tampoco fueron así los años anteriores. así que de este no voy a quejarme, me ha hecho salir de mi zona de confort más de una vez, echarle ovarios a la vida, enfrentarme a mis miedos y lograr ser yo misma a pesar de mis miedos y mis inseguridades. 
puede que el 2018 haya terminado siendo una verdadera mierda por las últimas noticias en mi vida pero con permiso de los demás, esta vez cierro el año diciendo... ¡olé yo!

text:
❤️
i look back on 2018
what a year it has been
i broke with negativity 
and let positivity flow right in..
i’ve made choices 
one particular sad one
i broke off contact with my parents
knowing it had to be done..
i’ve shed so many tears 
got back on track of my life path
i found closure of a trauma
within my heart..
i’ve been on a rollercoaster of emotions 
embraced them every day
broke with unhealthy patterns 
along the way..
i’ve reclaimed my creativity 
which i had blocked since i was a child 
i let it run free
after all that time..
i’ve made choices
one particular good one
i decided to donate my love, creativity and money to children in need
for many years to come..
and now i look forward to 2019
trusting it will be a loving year 
positivity is what i take with me 
i did my work and laid a powerful foundation
couldn’t be more ready for the upcoming year of soul’s abundance 
so very grateful 
shoutout to the universe 
thank you!

stem_filter: 日のメイク . . *アイシャドウ* ar 3065 alhambra クセル リアルクローズシャドウ cs01 テラコッタブーティ olourpop supershockshadow side kick tudehous blingblingeyestick 09 パールゴールド . *マスカラ* oon ロングラッシュマスカラ03 バーガンディ . *チーク* issha イタルプリズムサテンチーク ピーチアベニュー . *リップ* ac リップスティック ubywootokyo . . rubi woo tokyoメインメイク❤️💄 . リップがマットで濃いめなので アイメイクは艶ナチュラルで✨ カラポとエチュードのせいで 結局アイメイク使ったら ナチュラルではないのだが😊 . アイライナーはパレットの右下↘️使って 柔らかな印象に😃 . rubi woo tokyoかわいいよぉー‼ マットだからやはり乾燥はしてしまう💦 今度からちゃんと保湿して使おう☝️ 上からレッドベリーグラムや ニュアンスチェンジグロス使っても 絶対かわいいだろうし ポンポン塗りでふんわり色のせても良さそう😆💕 . 流行りの動画もどうぞ💁 盛れるし見せたくないとこ隠せるし メイク具合も伝わるしいいねぇ👍 . . . リップ欲しい期間に突入したぁー💄 もう使わないかな、ときめかないかな と、思ったリップを保管していたんだけど 会社の人にあげたり売ったら かなり食い付きよくて 今リップ収納ゾーンスカスカ‼ . 人が使ったリップって人気ない と思ったけど皆意外と使うのね😃 . addiction予約したリップと lunasolのベージュリップと コスデコの赤リップと bobbi brownの赤リップと chanelの新しく出るルージュココ欲しい💄 . で、いくらになる❔💸💸💸 皆も欲しいよね👌 だよね👌byかーこちゃん 使い方合ってるんだっけ😂 かーこちゃんライブ楽しかった🎵 だけど来年は 心掛けないと‼️byあいちゃん . 誰かカウントダウンライブやってー🎍 . . .

text:
let's talk abuse awareness!  sometimes i hear people say: "i don't understand how you can be so naive having experienced so many cruel things in your life." . 
the thing is, i am not naive, i do understand what is happening around me.
. 
but i've been so angry and bitter before. if i did not believe in the good of mankind. if i did not believe that your strength is to be found in your ability to show kindness. i would not have been able to let go of all the hatred i once felt towards others and myself. i would not have dared to be vulnerable
. 
i accept being hurt from time to time by giving people the benefits of my doubts.  this because i truly feel and think that  the happiness i find one good person is worth ten times the anger
one person can generate.
. 
this is something i've learned the hard way.
. 
i'm not naive. i've lived. i've chosen to be open to new friendships and new experiences. why? because i have experienced so much darkness
.
.
.

text:
gender bias is undermining our social fabric and devalues all of us. it is not just a human rights issue it is a tremendous waste of the world’s human potential. by denying women equal rights, we deny half the population a chance to live life at its fullest. political, economic and social equality for women will benefit all the world’s citizens.

•eliminate all forms of violence against all women and girls in the public and private spheres, including trafficking and sexual and other types of exploitation
•eliminate all harmful practices, such as child, early and forced marriage and female genital mutilation.
•recognize and value unpaid care and domestic work through the provision of public services, infrastructure and social protection policies and the promotion of shared responsibility within the. household and the family as nationally appropriate
•ensure women’s full and effective participation and equal opportunities for leadership at all levels of decisionmaking in political, economic and public life.
•ensure universal access to sexual and reproductive health and reproductive rights .

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardia

text_retweet:
anthonia alasa-ojenagbon is a sexual abuse survivor. underneath her positive, never-say-die outlook on life lies a little girl whose innocence was taken away by someone she trusted.

thank you anthonia for speaking your truth.

#repost @toniabruisedbutnotbroken

a bishop sent me a message saying l should stop taking about sexual violence since god has helped me,now l am married(in his words) he went as far as advising me  not to bring shame on the man who married me. in his words the man did me a great favor. 
this is my response, sir with all due respect l will not stop talking. i will continue to lend my voice ,l will continue to speak out  against rape ,molestation,incest or any form of sexual violence until something is done. i am a christian girl who is not ashamed to speak out. 
our dear ochanya died after being violated sexually for years by father and son 😭😭 and some people still think talking about this does not make sense? how many more innocent children will die before we know there is an emergency? most sexual violence cases are perpetrated by people the victims know. because of society's shame,stigma and judgement most survivors never speak. the number of survivors who have spoken is nothing compared to the ones who have never spoken about their abuse. we will not keep quiet. 
sexual violence can have harmful and lasting consequences for the victims,families, communities.  sexual violence victimisation is associated with several health risk behaviour. the effects can have psychological,emotional,and physical effects on a survivor. the effects are not easy to deal,it can take a life time to heal. with the right help and support survivors can be managed.

sexual violence is not a joke,it should never be trivialised.  we will not be silenced. our voice,our power.... to everyone who has survived, l salute you big time. i salute your courage. i salute your strength. we survived the abuse,we will definitely survive the recovery . our lives matter. 
#metoomovement #metoo #notoviolenceagainstwomen #nigerianfeminist #irememberabuse #unmutted #awakening #nomore

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates suppoed by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

cu devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text_retweet:
🙏 #repost @julie.vasa with @get_repost
・・・ 📚❤️ #uneanneedelivres - jour 10 - le livre le plus inattendu : une carte postale du bonheur, de @cristina_de_a , @editions_seramis ➡️ https://lapostrophee.com/une-carte-postale-du-bonheur-cristina-de-amorim (lien en bio)
▪️▪️▪️▪️◽️
alors même que la parole des femmes s’est récemment libérée avec le mouvement #metoo, les cas de violence conjugale demeurent trop nombreux en france. des femmes meurent sous les coups de leurs conjoints, c’est une réalité. parmi eux, certains s’avèrent extrêmement pernicieux puisqu’ils sont moins visibles mais tout aussi destructeurs, les cas de violence verbale et psychologique. étonnement, « une carte postale du bonheur » met en scène de manière particulièrement réussie et réaliste l’un de ces cas. mais pourquoi ai-je spécifié « étonnement » ?
🔸
cette lecture a commencé par des échanges virtuels sur instagram, entre cristina et moi, toutes deux passionnées de littérature… apercevant un jour une photo de cristina prise à gruyère en suisse, une ville charmante pas très éloignée de genève, nous avons échangé quelques mots, puis nous sommes rencontrées pour la première fois lors de la soirée du grand prix des blogueurs littéraires il y a un an. cristina a proposé de m’adresser son livre qu’elle venait d’achever, son premier ! reçu quelques jours après, je ne l’ai pourtant pas ouvert avant plusieurs mois alors même que cet envoi m’avait ravie. pourquoi ? sans aucun doute la couverture et le titre. on y découvre une femme au bord de la crise de nerfs, bigoudis sur la tête et maquillage dégoulinant… je m’attendais à un bon feel good, que je me réservais comme lecture facile pour un moment de détente lors d’une période tendue. mon déménagement fut l’occasion idéale !
🔸
et là, une révélation : « une carte postale du bonheur » est à cent lieues de ce que j’imaginais ! une très agréable surprise pour un roman fort, intelligent, mettant en scène une femme sous emprise d’une relation toxique (suite du post dans les commentaires 👇🏻).
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
#bookstagram #instabook #instalivre #livrestagram #igreads #igbooks #bookaddict #roman #livreaddict #book #litterature #premierroman

text: eftersom jag fyller år den 26:e och nyåret är några dagar senare så hinner jag fundera lite på året som gått. och jäklarns vad det gått! jag har föreläst från kiruna till trelleborg. träffat så många pedagoger, elever, socialtjänsthandläggare, länsstyrelser och jourkvinnor (och alla däremellan). fick chans att åka till marocko med @unicefsverige och @mama.nu för att få en förståelse för hur mödravården och unga kvinnors vardag ser ut (med stora mängder sexuellt våld och utsatthet). jag drog ihop en manifestation mot sexuellt våld med fantastiska talare och medarrangörer dit över 3000 personer kom med 🎀 om halsen. lämnade in 26.000 underskrifter till @johanssonmorgan70 om en obligatorisk utbildning kring sexualbrott för rättsväsendet. samtyckeslagen klubbades äntligen igenom! och jag fick ta emot ett pris för mitt arbete i madeleine leijonhufvuds anda. och 2018 var också året då vi tvingades begrava madeleine 💔 och samtidigt: vi fick se ett helt nytt liv! jag födde vår älskade bonsan ❤️ som (en hel del tack vare @peter_svensson_ ) blev till under brinnande #metoo som jag också debatterade och kommenterade under året. vår andra bejbis @huskurage växte och ännu fler kommuner och bostadsbolag bidrog till att fler vet hur de kan agera för att uppmärksamma och hjälpa utsatta barn och vuxna. ————————————————————————- en argt skrikande man med en videokamera och swishkonto spred påhitt om mig som bidrog till massa hat och en del hot. därtill skrev rasistiska sajter än mer påhitt som plockades upp av ett parti som fått nästan var femte röst och som innebar ännu mer hat och hot. under året blev det också tydligt hur unga killar och män väljer att hata och hota kvinnor i ”idrottens namn”. det gjorde mig än mer övertygad om vikten av att fortsätta debattera och kommentera. att stå upp för frågorna om sexism, kvinnohat, övergrepp, rasism och sexuellt våld. och det blev också tydligt att det finns många som backar och peppar. så tack alla ni som fortsätter kämpa, peppa och stå upp mot sexism, homofobi och rasism. som agerar när ni är oroliga för en medmänniska. tillsammans gör vi skillnad! ❤️✊

nevertheless, all cameras turned out like this..... fml

text:
#women that made my #2018.

le #donne del 2018.

1. @jacindaardern , attuale primo ministro della nuova zelanda e leader del partito laburista, mentre allatta la sua figlia in seduta parlamentare com accanto il marito. 
2. #frances hamilton arnold, biochimica e ingegneria statunitense, premio nobel @nobelprize_org per la chimica del 2018, "per i loro lavori su enzimi, peptidi e anticorpi" contributo per la cura cancro. nel 2005 le è stato diagnosticato un cancro al seno, che ha sconfitto.

3. il #g7, la #merkel e la classe. no comment! 
4. margherita #pagani, ceo di #impacton @impactonorg , un network che consente di conoscere e diffondere le idee a impatto sociale migliori. scopre come i modelli che funzionano devono poter essere applicati a livello locale. parte dall'esempio dei rifugiati di #idromeni, in grecia. 
5. letizia @letiziabattaglia_anthologia (palermo, 5 marzo 1935) è
"la fotografa della mafia". le sue foto, spesso in un vivido e nitido bianco e nero, si prefiggono di raccontare soprattutto palermo nella sua miseria e nel suo splendore, i suoi morti di mafia ma anche le sue tradizioni, gli sguardi di bambini e donne. 
6. il movimento #metoo è un movimento di matrice femminista che verte contro le molestie e la violenza sulle donne. nel 2018, non solo le donne parlano delle loro esperienze ma gli autori dei reati sono chiamati a rendere conto delle loro azioni.

#buonanno, #donne, #2018, #woman #power, #speakout, #consigli, #coscienza #storia

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
a few months later, in autumn 2013, wylie met steve bannon. at the time, he was editor-in-chief of breitbart, which he had brought to britain to support his friend nigel farage in his mission to take britain out of the european union.

what was he like? - smart, says wylie. - interesting. really interested in ideas. he’s the only straight man i’ve ever talked to about intersectional feminist theory. he saw its relevance straightaway to the oppressions that conservative, young white men feel.

wylie meeting bannon was the moment petrol was poured on a flickering flame. wylie lives for ideas. he speaks 19 to the dozen for hours at a time. he had a theory to prove. and at the time, this was a purely intellectual problem. politics was like fashion, he told bannon.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
a few months later, in autumn 2013, wylie met steve bannon. at the time, he was editor-in-chief of breitbart, which he had brought to britain to support his friend nigel farage in his mission to take britain out of the european union.

what was he like? - smart, says wylie. - interesting. really interested in ideas. he’s the only straight man i’ve ever talked to about intersectional feminist theory. he saw its relevance straightaway to the oppressions that conservative, young white men feel.

wylie meeting bannon was the moment petrol was poured on a flickering flame. wylie lives for ideas. he speaks 19 to the dozen for hours at a time. he had a theory to prove. and at the time, this was a purely intellectual problem. politics was like fashion, he told bannon.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
📚❤️ #uneanneedelivres - jour 10 - le livre le plus inattendu : une carte postale du bonheur, de @cristina_de_a , @editions_seramis ➡️ https://lapostrophee.com/une-carte-postale-du-bonheur-cristina-de-amorim (lien en bio)
▪️▪️▪️▪️◽️
alors même que la parole des femmes s’est récemment libérée avec le mouvement #metoo, les cas de violence conjugale demeurent trop nombreux en france. des femmes meurent sous les coups de leurs conjoints, c’est une réalité. parmi eux, certains s’avèrent extrêmement pernicieux puisqu’ils sont moins visibles mais tout aussi destructeurs, les cas de violence verbale et psychologique. étonnement, « une carte postale du bonheur » met en scène de manière particulièrement réussie et réaliste l’un de ces cas. mais pourquoi ai-je spécifié « étonnement » ?
🔸
cette lecture a commencé par des échanges virtuels sur instagram, entre cristina et moi, toutes deux passionnées de littérature… apercevant un jour une photo de cristina prise à gruyère en suisse, une ville charmante pas très éloignée de genève, nous avons échangé quelques mots, puis nous sommes rencontrées pour la première fois lors de la soirée du grand prix des blogueurs littéraires il y a un an. cristina a proposé de m’adresser son livre qu’elle venait d’achever, son premier ! reçu quelques jours après, je ne l’ai pourtant pas ouvert avant plusieurs mois alors même que cet envoi m’avait ravie. pourquoi ? sans aucun doute la couverture et le titre. on y découvre une femme au bord de la crise de nerfs, bigoudis sur la tête et maquillage dégoulinant… je m’attendais à un bon feel good, que je me réservais comme lecture facile pour un moment de détente lors d’une période tendue. mon déménagement fut l’occasion idéale !
🔸
et là, une révélation : « une carte postale du bonheur » est à cent lieues de ce que j’imaginais ! une très agréable surprise pour un roman fort, intelligent, mettant en scène une femme sous emprise d’une relation toxique (suite du post dans les commentaires 👇🏻).
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
#bookstagram #instabook #instalivre #livrestagram #igreads #igbooks #bookaddict #roman #livreaddict #book #litterature #premierroman #violenceconjugale #emprise #perversnarcissique

text:
京都にある性被害の自助グループ「mint（ミント）」1月の活動予定のお知らせです❤︎
.
.
【self help group】
.
2019年1月19日（土）
13:00〜16:00
.
.
女性として生きる中で感じていることを気軽に話せる場所です。批判やアドバイスはせず、話すほうも聞くほうもお互いにありのままで受け止めます。主に性的なトラウマを抱える女性（女性の心をもつ方）を対象としていますが、性被害のご経験の有無に関わらず女性として生きてきた中で向き合いたいことやお話ししたいことがあるときに足を運んでみてくださいね。
.
（場所）
京都駅中央改札口より徒歩約12分
「しんらん交流館」1f会議室
.
（参加費）
500円  献金制
.
（お申し込み）
参加ご希望の方は下記①〜④の事項を添えてメールにてお申し込みください。折り返しご連絡いたします。
①メールの件名「ミント参加希望」
②お名前（ニックネーム可）
③メールアドレス
④ご希望の日程
selfhelpgroup.mint@gmail.com
.
会場へのアクセスなど自助グループについて詳細はプロフィール欄（ @selfhelpgroup_mint ）ホームページの「self help group」をご覧ください。
.
.
【online salon】
.
2019年1月22日（火） meeting
.
.
遠方の方や直接会うことに抵抗がある場合はオンラインサロンでもお話しすることができます。月に1回のミーティングのほか、お気に入りの音楽や写真をアップしたり自分の体験を綴ったり、ネット上に開設した当事者のためのサロンです。（サロンは性被害のご経験をもつ女性（女性の心をもつ方）専用としております。）
.
オンラインサロンについての詳細はプロフィール欄（ @selfhelpgroup_mint ）ホームページの「online salon」をご覧ください。
.
.
お話しできることを楽しみにしています(*^^*)
.
self help group「mint」
野間千華子
.
.
.

text:
instagram рассказал о значимых трендах и определила самые популярные явления 2018 года. 
самая популярная наклейка в stories – фирменный стикер instagram-лайка с сердечком. 
самый популярный фильтр в stories – heart eyes, который изображает влюблённые глаза. 
наиболее популярный эмодзи – символ сердца ❤️, который использовался более 14 миллиардов раз. 
самое счастливое место на земле – токийский диснейленд. это звание он получил благодаря анализу использования улыбчивых эмодзи среди геолокаций. 
самое популярное танцевальное движение – #inmyfeelingschallenge. в нем поучаствовали знаменитости. 
самый быстрорастущий тэг в мире – #fortnite из-за роста известности игры fortnite
также среди популярных тэгов – #metoo (1,5 млн использований), #timesup (597 тыс. использований) и #marchforourlives (562 тыс. использований). #молнияэтоинтересно #madeontilda #сайтнатильде #flashtilda #разработкасайтов #сайт #лендинг #новыйгод

text:
as we continue to review the highlights of 2018, we are awed by the courage and tenacity of nadia murad.  ms. murad was awarded the 2018 nobel peace prize (with denis mukwege) and is the witness who tells of the abuses perpetrated against herself and others. she has shown uncommon courage in recounting her own sufferings and speaking up on behalf of other victims. 
an excerpt of her nobel lecture "let us all unite to fight injustice and oppression; let us raise our voices together and say: no to violence, yes to peace, no to slavery, yes to freedom, no to racial discrimination, yes to equality and to human rights for all.
no to exploiting women and children, yes to providing a decent and independent life to them, no to impunity for criminals, yes to holding criminals accountable and to achieving justice." (nobel acceptance lecture)

text: throughout this entire process, i felt like i've had no control. even when i'm given control in the reporting process at my school, in therapy, in how i tell my story to you, it doesn't feel like control: it feels like a train with no tracks. i have no idea what i'm doing, i have no idea what i need, i don't even know what i am capable of doing. i don't know the rules i'm supposed to follow or what everything is supposed to look like. but that's the thing about sexual assault and recovery-- there is no textbook case. there isn't one way to do it. each storm is a little different, but that doesn't mean we can't learn how to navigate the water amid the turmoil. that's where the control is: i get to decide what my goals are for reporting, what changes i want to see in my life and mental health, and how my story is told. i get to make my own tracks. i may not have had control over what happened to me, but i get to decide where i go from here. and that is incredibly comforting #comfort #confidence #control #rules #oceanside #ocean #sailing #recovery #inspiration #motivation #instaquote #instagood #mylife #mythoughts #writersofinstagram #positivevibes #thoughts #learning #learn #poetrycommunity #writing #thoughts #thoughtoftheday #positivequotes #positivity #positivethinking #mylife #me #mentalhealth #mentalhealthawareness #metoo #anxiety

text:
what even is healing anyway? ➡️please swipe to read about my perceptions of healing➡️
(sorry this is like super long, i just wanted to be real with you all)
throughout the past year since i was raped, i have defined healing in many ways in a desperate attempt to feel like i have "solved the problem" of my ptsd, anxiety, depression, flashbacks and nightmares. i wanted to feel in control. i wanted to feel like i could "fix" myself. but truthfully, there is no "fixing" trauma. all of these perceptions of healings left me feeling  just as broken. i am not fully sure what healing will look like for me. but i'm not sure if i believe it will ever be something that feels like it can be completed.
leave a 🌹 below if you read the entire post.

text:
carmen maria machado
author
—
i finally read carmen maria machado's collection of short stories, "her body and other parties" over the holiday, and it knocked my head clean off. each story is a haunting chronicle of the way women have learned to inhabit physical bodies in this patriarchal world. carmen's stories are metaphysical in a way that feels so natural. they feel like equal parts science fiction, and science fact - just like a female body often does. pick up this book, and devour it when the time is right. (pro tip: brush up on your law & order)
.
from @vulture - as the world began to pay attention to women’s stories of abuse, her queer, liminal stories held a flickering candle to the subtle forms of cruelty that continue to go undiscussed.
.
it is impossible to know how machado’s stories would have been received in another era, but in this one, they have reverberated among readers with the prophetic force of a soothsayer’s divinations. “the way she arcs so gracefully from gothic romance to comedy to horror, feels true to me of how we live our lives,” the author karen russell, a fan, told me in an email. “a life story is multi-genre, and in the course of a day your love story might turn into a horror story, or vice versa.”
.
machado’s fiction is richest when it delves into those internal, haunting moments that mark a woman’s life. as russell put it, her work shows “how the violence migrates inward, from the wider culture into women’s private minds and bodies. it’s wonderful that we have these stories in the era of metoo, when there is a need and an appetite for the truths that only fiction can tell,” russell added.
.
this short article excerpt doesn't do justice to how deeply machado is writing about this incredible moment in time. she has been both an advocate and critic of the #metoo movement. her writing is where the rubber hits the road of women's stories. they are not easy to tell, not easy to hear, but absolutely necessary. lest we begin to fade away.
—
#dailyfeminist #carmenmariamachado #author #herbodyandother parties #bodies #misogyny #patriarchy #metoo #thehusbandstich #especiallyheinous #speakup #speakout #tellyourstory #wearehere

text:
this year has taught me a lot. a. lot. thank you everyone who has contributed to my positive growth, you know who you are... everything that happened also inspired me to be stronger and stand up for what i truly believe in.
more power to all the people who shared their #metoo experiences. 
more strength to those who are fighting the system, everyday. 
2019 has no room for casual sexism and  patriarchal bs and it's about time people get their act right, for there will be consequences. 
this new year let us do our bit, let's start with being sensitive and making the world more inclusive. i am determined and won't back down. join the team
.
.
.
 #ateam #genderequality #feminism #feminist #progress #healtheworld #positivevibes #smashthepatriarchy
.
.
.

.
＊「ラーレ・イスタンブール」について...
.
ラーレ (lale) とは...
トルコ語で「チューリップ」の意味。(先の尖ったトルコ原産のチューリップはトルコ伝統織物やセラミックのモチーフに愛用者されています。)
.
イスタンブール (istanbul) とは...
「コンスタンティノープル」の別名を有し、東洋と西洋が交差するトルコの古都。
.

text:
2018 akan segera berakhir dan seperti biasanya industri hiburan akan disibukkan dengan akhir tahun.

disaat ada banyak selebriti yang suksesn adapula beberapa yang terlibat dalam kontroversi dan menjatuhkan reputasi mereka. selama satu tahun ini, media sports today menyiapkan penghargaan 2018 dengan opini yang subjektif. 
berikut adalah selebriti yang terpilih menjadi "the worst person of the year". .
1. yang hyun suk: pembatalan debut 'mixnine'
"dengan kekuatan yg sebagai tiang, dia mengatakan akan mendebutkan dan menempatkan trainee dalam kompetisi. namun ia membatalkan debut mereka karena program itu gagal. dia menciptakan kontroversi dengan menanggapinya dengan mengambil tindakan hukum lewat gugatan balik. kemudian bahkan setahun kemudian, ia menciptakan acara audisi yang sama 'yg treasure box.' ide ironisnya mengejutkan semua orang. " - reporter yoon hye young.

2. lee seo won: pelecehan seksual
"tingkah lakunya yang berani setelah pelecehan seksual, ketidaktahuan terus-menerus, dan terakhir, tindakannya melarikan diri ke militer. aku terkejut 3 kali." - reporter kim sat byul

3. kim saeng min: #metoo
"dia menghabiskan waktu emas yang ditunggu-tunggu dalam 25 tahun. kau mendapatkan apa yang kamu berikan." - reporter kim na yeon

4. nancy lang x wang: pernikahan dan perceraian yang kontroversial
"pembuat masalah dengan perkawinan, perkelahian, dan perceraian yang gaduh." - reporter han ye ji

5  lee jin min cp: manipulasi 'heart signal 2' "dia menciptakan program viral 'heart signal' tetapi ada juga banyak kontroversi. dia bahkan lebih mengecewakan penonton dengan perilakunya yang tidak menyenangkan dalam wawancara tentang kesalahan siaran, manipulasi dalam penyuntingan, dan banyak lagi." - reporter moon soo yeon

6. microdot: penipuan orang tua
"orang tuanya berbohong kepada orang-orang di kota mereka, putranya berbohong kepada pemirsa." - reporter kim hyun min

bagaimana menurut kalian?
.

text: watching @johntravolta practice his riding on the #mechanicalbull in the movie #urbancowboy ❤️’d him, @bonnieraittofficial music and this movie as a teenager. the soundtrack is great! heard the song #mamadontletyourbabiesgrowuptobecowboys in this movie with @wingerdebra . #coincidence in casting her in @theranchnetflix #theranch theme song years later? i think not! other things you notice when you watch old movies...the women, especially her character, is beaten and abused by both her male love interests and it’s considered romantic. makes you realize how common it was and not really addressed much in the movie. glad to see her playing a much stronger character (better #femalerolemodelling ) in #theranch .the fact is that this #metoo movement is nothing new men! don’t be scared about it! stand by the women in your life who talk about their experiences. that could be your #sister #mother #friend #grandmother #aunt .it’s just being talked about more and less acceptable but it’s been the reality for most women growing up in some form of another. any girl who was ever followed home from school? i know several #standbythewomeninyourlife

text:
2018.... it was the year of #metoo, pay equity, and our prime minister becoming a mum. it was the year a female rugby player - at last - gained the sport's top honour. it was the 125th anniversary of suffrage, a year of celebration. but also a reminder that change does not come without hard work and frustration.... all year, we have watched as new zealand women have fought for their rights. and fought..... and fought.... from campaigning against sexual harassment in the media, to arguing for equal pay through the courts, to addressing our shameful domestic violence record at the united nations, women stood up and were counted. they raised their voices when others didn't want to hear. they were empowered in the face of adversity. they persisted despite knowing meaningful change would likely be a long time yet.

that persistence has led us to name women - all women - as our 2018 new zealanders of the year. #women #newzealandersoftheyear #metoo #payequity #equality #payparity. #un #nzwomen #nz #domesticviolence #womenssuffrage #one_womans_view #womeninmedicine

text:
rp @aknevenka 
rp @aknevenka on mother's day i want to make them visible.  to those mothers who live under constant pregnancies but they never see their young grow up.  those slave mothers who spend their days hooked to a suction machine, to which the udders are detached and send them to kill because "they no longer serve".
.
the invisible mothers, those who spend days calling their calves without knowing or knowing that they also do not walk towards freedom.

i recorded the images the first time i entered a tambo. in chivilcoy, province of buenos aires.  en el día de la madre quiero visibilizarlas a ellas.
a esas mujeres que viven sometidas a constantes embarazos
pero que nunca ven crecer a sus crías.
a esas mujeres esclavas que pasan sus días enganchadas a una máquina succionadora,
a las que se les desprenden las ubres y las mandan a matar porque “ya no sirven”.
.
las madres invisibles,
las que pasan días llamando a sus terneros
sin saber o sabiendo que ellxs tampoco caminan hacia la libertad.

las imágenes las grabé la primera vez que entré a un tambo. en chivilcoy, provincia de buenos aires. #dairyfree #dairy #govegan #crueltyfree #meat #hamburger #burger #pizzahut #pizzapizza #ilovepizza #cheesecake #cheesecakefactory #cheesey #cheeseboard #creamy #cream #creamcheese #dairyisscary #stopseparatingfamilies #burgerking #tacobell #burrito #quesadilla #vegano #metoo #seperation #donttakeourplanetforgranted

text:
i used to care about what people would think.
.
okay, i still do because i’m human (duh) but it took an “internet troll” to make some unfriendly comment about my picture to realize that the sting lasted exactly .1 seconds and i was able to respectfully respond then bless and release it. there was a time that would’ve brought on anxiety and pushed me so far back from the progress i made to care less of others opinions.
.
because let me tell you something sister. no one else’s opinion of how you’re choosing to do life will get you to where you want to be. are you listening? their opinion on your job, parenting, physique, faith....matters zero%.
.
do you have big goals that you’re burying and pushing down because you’re scared to say them out loud for fear of what someone else will think? declare your business success! set that non-scale victory! go to the marriage conference! do the big scary thing if it is going to allow you to live the life you dream of!
.
4 years ago i was a worn out, perfectionist mama of the biggest crybaby ever who was returning to a full time job that paid nothing for my degree that decided to take on a business venture that would hold me accountable to my own self-care while allowing me to squirrel away for a sahm fund. what i’ve received back from that big scary yes is almost no back pain, stronger body (even after 2 babies), major confidence boost, new friends, leaning into my calling to counsel others all while being a wife and mama first.
.
babe - i know you’re scared to leap. but trust the girl who said no for a year who wishes she had said yes all along.
.

name: G A B B Y  L A S S I T E R
tweet_full:
i used to care about what people would think.
.
okay, i still do because i’m human (duh) but it took an “internet troll” to make some unfriendly comment about my picture to realize that the sting lasted exactly .1 seconds and i was able to respectfully respond then bless and release it. there was a time that would’ve brought on anxiety and pushed me so far back from the progress i made to care less of others opinions.
.
because let me tell you something sister. no one else’s opinion of how you’re choosing to do life will get you to where you want to be. are you listening? their opinion on your job, parenting, physique, faith....matters zero%.
.
do you have big goals that you’re burying and pushing down because you’re scared to say them out loud for fear of what someone else will think? declare your business success! set that non-scale victory! go to the marriage conference! do the big scary thing if it is going to allow you to live the life you dream of!
.
4 years ago i was a worn out, perfectionist mama of the biggest crybaby ever who was returning to a full time job that paid nothing for my degree that decided to take on a business venture that would hold me accountable to my own self-care while allowing me to squirrel away for a sahm fund. what i’ve received back from that big scary yes is almost no back pain, stronger body (even after 2 babies), major confidence boost, new friends, leaning into my calling to counsel others all while being a wife and mama first.
.
babe - i know you’re scared to leap. but trust the girl who said no for a year who wishes she had said yes all along.
.

to my risers - you changed the course of history. here’s to all the flowers growing through concrete. to all the ones scared but doing it anyway. to those who answer the call to serve, the call to love our brothers and sisters, despite our differences in creed, color or belief. here’s to those who believe beyond our capacity to know as human beings with certainty what lies ahead of us, and yet charge forth heeding a call to create a better world. 20 laws. change is possible. impossible is only an opinion. call on, world. we, risers, will be there to heed it. thanks for the love, @forbes.

i am outraged that the violence against women act (vawa) has officially expired due to the partial government shutdown.

since 1994 the vawa has protected victims of domestic violence and sexual assault and was the first federal legislation to recognize and address domestic violence as a serious crime. domestic violence and sexual assault programs funded by vawa will be cut off until the legislation is reauthorized.

as a domestic violence survivor, advocate and activist, i am utterly disappointed. you'll be hearing more from me on this topic. i'll never stop fighting for what's right.

#domesticviolenceawareness #sexualassaultawareness
#advocacyalert #advocacy 
#victimrights #metoo 
#stopviolenceagainstwomen
#timesup #vawa #nomore 
#thestillstandingalliance

text:
t h r e e // ways to listen to your gut 
#advocate #idaho——————————————————————
your intuition is trying to warn you of danger. are you ignoring it?
it’s likely we’ve all met that person at some point in our lives that makes us take a pause and think. “hold on, something seems off here.”
at this point, we have two choices: listen to our gut or ignore it.
gavin de becker renown security expert and author of the bestselling the gift or fear, based his book entirely on not ignoring those warnings. but, says bob martin, retired los angeles police department captain turned senior advisor for gavin de becker & associates, “human beings are the only creatures on earth that will override their intuition.”
your intuition could save you from a sexual predator, a rapist, a kidnapper, or a manipulative, abusive partner. listening to it could very well save your life. 
the question is, then, how can we stop overriding our intuition? in this slider, martin explains three ways we can better listen to our gut. —————————————————————— #lifestyle #family #loveshouldnthurt #december #enddv #byui #dvfacts #dancing #entrepreneur #fall #design #wellness #marketing #friends #idaho #timesup #metoo #idaho #health #breakthesilence #idaho #graphicdesign #healthy #winter #christmas

text:
think vogue and the mind immediately conjures images of men and women dressed in designer clothes. the vogue women of the year 2018 awards was no different.however, the one lady that stood out in her crpf uniform was 28-year-old usha kiran.

this lady singham is the youngest female crpf officer to be a part of commando battalion for resolute action (cobra) and is currently serving the volatile region of bastar in chhattisgarh. during her training period, she requested her seniors to allow her to serve under the male battalion in an extreme left-wing infested state, or j&k, or north-east front areas. finally, she was given chhattisgarh region, bastar a district dreaded with maoist activities. also in her spare time, she helps the school going girls in their studies.

she is an inspiration to many and a role model for young tribal women in joining the armed forces.
sources: indiatimes & thebetterindia.com

text:
kita butuh uu yang akan membarier kita dari persoalan-persoalan kekerasan seksual terhadap perempuan, dan siapapun itu.

indonesia sedang darurat kekerasan seksual. berbagai kasus kekerasan seksual tidak mendapat ruang keadilan dimata hukum.  konstruksi berpikir yg timpang dan dominasi relasi kuasa menyebabkan superioritas patriarki masih menjamur dalam segala lini.

pun soal budaya konservatisme yang berjalan kelindan dengan budaya patriarki sedang sama-sama merawat stigma negatif bagi korban kekerasan seksual.

korban cenderung distigma sebagai pemicu atas persoalan yang dialami. padahal, korban butuh dampingan dan keadilan dimata hukum.

kita menginginkan negara ini, sadar hukum dan adil gender. segra sahkan ruu penghapusan kekerasan seksual !!! menangkan pancasila
wujudkan kesetaraan gender dan kesejahteraan sosial

tina turner bullock #swisssisters #lindorchocolate the púca (irish for spirit/#ghost), pooka, phouka, phooka, phooca, puca or púka is primarily a creature of celtic folklore.[1] considered to be bringers both of good and bad fortune, they could either help or hinder rural and marine communities. the púca can have dark or white fur or hair. the creatures were said to be shape changers which could take the appearance of #horses, goats, cats, dogs, and #hares. they may also take a human form, which includes various animal features, such as ears or a tail.
the púca has counterparts throughout the celtic cultures of #northwest europe. for instance, in welsh mythology it is named the pwca and in cornish the bucca.[2] in the channel islands, the pouque were said to be fairies who lived near ancient stones; in channel island french a cromlech, or prehistoric tomb, is referred to as a pouquelée or pouquelay(e); poulpiquet and polpegan are corresponding terms in #brittany.the origin of the name may have come from the #oldnorse term pook or puki, which refers to a "nature spirit". usage of the term in ireland, however, may predate the arrival of #norse settlers.[5] in germanic languages, such as#frisian or english, this became pucel, pook or #puck. the name of the pooka may also come from the irish word poc, meaning a male goat, a form the creature is often said to take.there are stories of some púca being blood-thirsty and vampire-like creatures. other stories even say some are man-eating beings, hunting down, killing, and eating their victims.
morphology and physiology
according to legend, the púca is a deft shapeshifter, capable of assuming a variety of terrifying or pleasing forms. it can take a human form, but will often have animal features, such as ears or a tail.[12] as an animal, the púca will most commonly appear as a horse, cat,#rabbit, raven,#fox, wolf, goat, goblin, or dog. no matter what shape the púca takes, its fur is almost always dark. it most commonly takes the form of a sleek black horse with a flowing mane and luminescent golden eyes.[13] (the manx glashtyn also takes on human form, but he usually betrays his horse's ears and is analogous to the each u

text:
tina turner bullock #swisssisters #lindorchocolate the púca (irish for spirit/#ghost), pooka, phouka, phooka, phooca, puca or púka is primarily a creature of celtic folklore.[1] considered to be bringers both of good and bad fortune, they could either help or hinder rural and marine communities. the púca can have dark or white fur or hair. the creatures were said to be shape changers which could take the appearance of #horses, goats, cats, dogs, and #hares. they may also take a human form, which includes various animal features, such as ears or a tail.
the púca has counterparts throughout the celtic cultures of #northwest europe. for instance, in welsh mythology it is named the pwca and in cornish the bucca.[2] in the channel islands, the pouque were said to be fairies who lived near ancient stones; in channel island french a cromlech, or prehistoric tomb, is referred to as a pouquelée or pouquelay(e); poulpiquet and polpegan are corresponding terms in #brittany.the origin of the name may have come from the #oldnorse term pook or puki, which refers to a "nature spirit". usage of the term in ireland, however, may predate the arrival of #norse settlers.[5] in germanic languages, such as#frisian or english, this became pucel, pook or #puck. the name of the pooka may also come from the irish word poc, meaning a male goat, a form the creature is often said to take.there are stories of some púca being blood-thirsty and vampire-like creatures. other stories even say some are man-eating beings, hunting down, killing, and eating their victims.
morphology and physiology
according to legend, the púca is a deft shapeshifter, capable of assuming a variety of terrifying or pleasing forms. it can take a human form, but will often have animal features, such as ears or a tail.[12] as an animal, the púca will most commonly appear as a horse, cat,#rabbit, raven,#fox, wolf, goat, goblin, or dog. no matter what shape the púca takes, its fur is almost always dark. it most commonly takes the form of a sleek black horse with a flowing mane and luminescent golden eyes.[13] (the manx glashtyn also takes on human form, but he usually betrays his horse's ears and is analogous to the each u

tina turner bullock #swisssisters #lindorchocolate the púca (irish for spirit/#ghost), pooka, phouka, phooka, phooca, puca or púka is primarily a creature of celtic folklore.[1] considered to be bringers both of good and bad fortune, they could either help or hinder rural and marine communities. the púca can have dark or white fur or hair. the creatures were said to be shape changers which could take the appearance of #horses, goats, cats, dogs, and #hares. they may also take a human form, which includes various animal features, such as ears or a tail.
the púca has counterparts throughout the celtic cultures of #northwest europe. for instance, in welsh mythology it is named the pwca and in cornish the bucca.[2] in the channel islands, the pouque were said to be fairies who lived near ancient stones; in channel island french a cromlech, or prehistoric tomb, is referred to as a pouquelée or pouquelay(e); poulpiquet and polpegan are corresponding terms in #brittany.the origin of the name may have come from the #oldnorse term pook or puki, which refers to a "nature spirit". usage of the term in ireland, however, may predate the arrival of #norse settlers.[5] in germanic languages, such as#frisian or english, this became pucel, pook or #puck. the name of the pooka may also come from the irish word poc, meaning a male goat, a form the creature is often said to take.there are stories of some púca being blood-thirsty and vampire-like creatures. other stories even say some are man-eating beings, hunting down, killing, and eating their victims.
morphology and physiology

text:
las mujeres no paran de pelear

no hay nada nuevo en 'revenge" y eso la hace mejor película aún. la francesa coralie  fargeat debuta por la puerta grande tomando un subgénero del terror, el rape and revenge, y nos regala una obra visualmente poderosa y de ritmo trepidante.

es curioso como un momento histórico puede empujar mucho más a un filme. la historia de una mujer, en apariencia débil, que decide vengarse de sus abusadores es tan vieja como el propio cine. títulos como 'a cruel picture', 'i spit on your grave', 'la última casa a la izquierda' o 'demented' así lo demuestran. de todas ellas bebe 'kill bill', la cinta de quentin tarantino. pero en plena explosión del #metoo, 'revenge' toma un nuevo sentido.

para los que no saben, el rape and revenge tiene una estructura clásica: abuso-muerte (en apariencia)-resurrección y venganza. fargeat toma estos elementos y con una banda sonora muy ochentera y paisajes muy bien estructurados, genera un ambiente ideal para que matilda anna ingrid lutz se luzca (jen) se luzca en pantalla.

es una obra de tres personajes. los villanos están a la altura, aunque destaca el buen hacer del antagonista principal: el atractivo kevin janssens (richard). como es natural, estas películas no son una oda a la verosimilitud. se trata simplemente de disfrutar del ojo por ojo. sin embargo, si esta cinta ha sido tan alabada es precisamente por los detalles de la fotografía y cuidado en el montaje, algo que pocas veces se ve en este subgénero. así que aplausos para el debut de fargeat.

puntuación: 4 pulgas de 5.

text:
choose love daily. choose it for yourself & for others.
.
.
showing yourself love every single day will transform your life.
.
.
showing love to others every single day will transform your life.
.
.
if you are doing those 2 things, there's no way your life won't change. .
.
some ideas for yourself: daily meditation, choosing healthy food daily, working out daily, yoga daily, daily affirmations, reading positive books, prayer, taking a bath, relaxing, getting pampered, alone time, sleep, doing your hair & makeup. so so many more, that's a start!
.
.
some ideas for others: random acts of kindness to strangers, doing something you don't want to do but will to show another love, your significant others love language, calling an old friend, calling a grandparent or parent, bringing food to someone sick or new parent, buying a gift as a surprise, writing a letter or card for no reason. .
.

text:
vete a la primera. siempre en la primera.

en la primera que te diga que no te arregles, que no te vistas así o que no te pongas eso...
en la primera que te menosprecie en público o en privado. 
vete a la primera que notes que necesita medirse el pito con los demás a costa tuya.
la primera vez que te demuestre que tu tienes más obligaciones y menos derechos que él. 
la primera vez que te preguntes porque siempre tienes que insistir para hacer algo juntos.
vete a la primera vez que en medio de una discusión le pegue a la pared o al mueble.
la primera vez que te vea divirtiéndote y te corte la alegría.
la primera vez que te vea brillando y no lo soporte. 
la primera vez que lo veas admirando a una mujer vestida con esa misma ropa que él no te deja usar.
la primera vez que te diga "'yo soy asi" aunque su manera de comportarse te duela.
la primera vez que te diga " le mueves las nalgas a todos"
la primera vez que te diga "vas a ir vestida asi".
la primera vez que te diga que "lo sacas de sus casillas" o que no te soporta 
la primera vez que te diga "lo hago por que te amo"
#vete
cuando te aplaste el ego y tu autoestima.
cuando te mate los sueños.
cuando se ría de tus ideas.
cuando no le importe si lo esperas.
cuando negativice tus planes.
cuando no tenga empatía.
cuando te mienta.
cuando te controle.
cuando te haga creer que eres difícil de amar. 
cuando le cueste acompañarte.
cuando te insulte.
cuando te humille. 
cuando no te tome en serio.
cuando minimice lo que te duele.
cuando te rompa.
cuando te culpe.
cuando te juzgue.
cuando se victimice siendo el culpable.
por favor... vete en la primera, siempre en la primera.
vas a encontrar a alguien mejor. vas a encontrar a alguien que mereces y te merezca.  #feminismo #feminista #mujer #chicas #girl #woman #girlpower #feminist #feminism #amor #love #frases #psicologia #salud #paz #autoestima

.
＊「ラーレ・イスタンブール」について...
.
ラーレ (lale) とは...
トルコ語で「チューリップ」の意味。(先の尖ったトルコ原産のチューリップはトルコ伝統織物やセラミックのモチーフに愛用者されています。)
.
イスタンブール (istanbul) とは...
「コンスタンティノープル」の別名を有し、東洋と西洋が交差するトルコの古都。
.

text:
.
.
ラーレ・イスタンブール (lale istanbul)は、トルコ製のインテリアやファッションアクセサリーを中心にセレクトしたアイテムをご紹介しております。.
.
＊「ラーレ・イスタンブール」について...
.
ラーレ (lale) とは...
トルコ語で「チューリップ」の意味。(先の尖ったトルコ原産のチューリップはトルコ伝統織物やセラミックのモチーフに愛用者されています。)
.
イスタンブール (istanbul) とは...
「コンスタンティノープル」の別名を有し、東洋と西洋が交差するトルコの古都。
.
ラーレ・イスタンブール 公式ブランドサイト
www.laleistanbul.com
.
onlinestore、twitter、facebookのフォローもどうぞ宜しくお願いいたします。

text:
#24speciesofcrane day 22

leucogeranus leucogeranus, leucogeranus leucogeranus, the siberian or snow crane. pictured above is likely the last specimen seen in north america as it perches in some sort of native #forage. 
the siberian crane migrates the furthest of any crane, each year finding their summer feeding grounds back in the ussr, where the western populations number less than 11, some counts suggest there are only four remaining cranes, dubbed the #fabfour. the cranes continue to be assassinated by hunters, fears that only three exist following entanglement with a japanese female are unconfirmed as yet. if thats not enough, there main food source are beatles, by some loose reference.

the snow goose call is normally described as a shrill #toyoya. some far eastern populations have translated this as "#toyota". eliyahu m goldratt asserts that the meticulous nest building techniques were copied exactly by taiichi ohno and eiji toyoda in their world leading production system, but herbie objects. 
the crane has always been a cultural leader in the area, the local shamans and shamanesses have been confirmed in many cases to be able to transform at will into these birds. really amazing stuff, exactly why we at #cranequarters started the #cranesarepeopletoo hashtag in the first place. 
some of the threats to the crane include so called #greenpower #hydro projects like the three rivers dam. other threats include hunting, agriculture and reindeer. further to this, farmers often shoot at the birds as they often eat the worms we require fore the biodynamic #veganfood we love.

why do the cranes not understand we are farming vegetables for their benefit, we dont want to revert to the #wrong ways of our ancestors and have to rely on meat and fish to grow healthy and strong. why cant they just join the #vegancrane cause and stop killing worms and fish?

#endtheextinction #creaseforpeace #fighttheman #metoo #endtheextinction #earthtoo #cranestoo #lgbqtc @peta @seashepherd #christmas #origami #vegetablepower #vegetable #vegancat #veganleopard
name: OG Crane Creaser

text:
يقف عام 2019 على الأبواب منتظرًا نهاية العام 2018 الذي شهد العديد من الأشياء المثيرة في عالم التقنية من بينها ما يتعلق بتطبيق إنستقرام واستمرار توسعه وتأثيره الاجتماعي على مئات الملايين من المستخدمين اليوميين، وهو ما ساهم في انتشار توجهات جديدة بين مجتمعات مختلفة.

وقد نشرت إنستقرام تقريرًا حول أهم التوجهات التي تفاعل معها المستخدمين خلال 2018، وتقول الشركة أن نشر الحب واللطف كانا العلامة الأهم بالنسبة للمستخدمين وهو ما يجعل بيئة التطبيق سعيدة، حيث أن “ ملصق القلب النابض بالحب من آراتا ” هو أكثر ملصق تم استخدامه على ميزة القصص “الستوريز”، فيما كان فلتر عينان على شكل قلب أكثر الفلاتر استخدامًا على القصص أيضًا. بينما تم استخدام فلتر القلب في التعليقات أكثر من 14 مليار مرة.

وبالحديث عن أسعد مكان بالعالم بالنسبة لمستخدمي إنستقرام، فإن مدينة ملاهي طوكيو ديزني هي صاحبة الامتياز.

وقالت الشركة أن مجتمع asmr مازال يحظى بشعبية هائلة طوال العام، حيث أن المجتمع يشهد ارتفاعًا كبيرًا بنشر مقاطع تقطيع الفيديو وفرقعة الفقاعات واستخدام مستحضرات التجميل وغيرها من الأمور التي تعمل على إراحة المستمع بحسب النظرية.

أما بالحديث عن الأمور الأخرى، فقد كان وسم #fortnite هو الأكثر شعبية على المنصة خلال العام، فيما كان التفاعل حول فرقة البوب الكورية bts هو الأكثر في المجال، بينما طغى تحدي كيكي على وسم #inmyfeelingschallenge على أكبر تحديات الرقص للعام.

على نفس الطريق، فقد كانت المنصة صاحبة رقعة كبيرة في مجال التأييد من أجل قضايا محددة، بحيث شهد وسم #metoo نحو 1.5 مليون تفاعل، فيما شهد وسم #timesup ما يقارب 597 ألف تفاعل، بينما شهد وسم #marchforourlives نحو 562 ألف تفاعل، وهو ما يؤكد قوة المنصة في التأثير على القضايا العامة.
#انستقرام #تطبيق #تحديث #سناب #سناب_شات #سنابيات #برامج #تصاميم #تصميمي #تقنية #تطبيقات #التطبيقات #الشروحات #الحلول

text:
i met marisol back in april at a mixer for my non-profit and women’s group, @girlpowerhoursa and even though she was a little quiet and shy i was impressed with her story and how she decided to pack up her life in dallas to pursue her dream of owning a coffee shop in her home city of san antonio. it didn’t take long for me to get to know her between her coming to gph-sa every month and me hanging out at the @thekoffeekupco to drink her delicious coffee creations with friends. ⠀
⠀
i’m super pumped to get to support a friend and a local san antonio business at the badass boss babe launch party on january 8th! marisol will be working her magic and making some custom coffee creations just for the brunch themed event, @eatkolaches will have some delicious kolaches and snacks for us, there will be a mimosa bar, and most of all we’ll have a fun party to kick off the podcast- san antonio style! 💃🏼 everyone is invited, so check out the link in my bio to rsvp and get more deets! ⠀
⠀

i’m super pumped to get to suppo a friend and a local san antonio business at the badass boss babe launch pay on january 8th! marisol will be working her magic and making some custom coffee creations just for the brunch themed event,  will have some delicious kolaches and snacks for us, there will be a mimosa bar, and most of all we’ll have a fun pay to kick off the podcast- san antonio style! 💃🏼 everyone is invited, so check out the link in my bio to rsvp and get more deets! ⠀
⠀

➡️in may 2018, the story that sparked #metoo showed the power of survivor voices when harvey weinstein was arrested for multiple sex crimes in the state of new york.

text:
i get a lot of people that ask me about zali’s father, some who i’ve known for years and others who are just curious. 
he is a man who wasn’t ready to take responsibility, who didn’t want anything to do with me except for the night zali was conceived , who isn’t really a man at all. 
he was given every option to be a part of zali’s life in whatever aspect he chose but he opted out and blocked all communication.

it’s his loss for not allowing himself to know this stunning girl and to watch her grow. it’s his loss for not being there to support her through the fight for her life when she was born too soon and to comfort her when she was sick or in pain. 
one day when zali is old enough i will tell her about him and how she was made. zali has a vast community of mums and dads to support me along the way and help her grow. 
#lovemygirl #singlemum #premmiebaby #babygirl #25weeker #25weekerpreemie #community #loveher #mysweetgirl #answeringquestions #heran #notarealman #metoo

text:
"este livro, entre manifestações efusivas por parte movimentos neo-nazis e de extrema direita, uma supremacia patriarcal branca, como demonstrada pela situação de países como o brasil e os estados unidos da própria bell hooks, a morte de marielle franco e a resistência de movimentos como o #metoo e black lives matter, mostra-se como uma poderosa arma de reflexão do lugar desta identidade, tantas vezes rasurada, das mulheres negras, apanhadas numa luta constante contra o imperialismo branco e patriarcal, à medida que tentam resistir às várias colonizações do corpo sofridas diariamente por mulheres, e em particular, as não brancas."
a @ana.bessa.carvalho debruça-se sobre este clássico de bell hooks, numa edição da @orfeunegroeditora 
link na bio.

text:
“women's empowerment is intertwined with respect for human rights.” -mahnaz afkhami
2018 was full of many ups and downs personally but i never imagined i’d ever get to live thru and experience the type of revival brought about by the #metoo movement and #timesup.
i believe women and men are equal in value but i am fortunate to be in relationship with jesus who is for the oppressed and there is no doubt women are often quite oppressed in society. it’s tragic that sexual assault happens to any human being, 91% of sexual assault happens to women.
we need to continue movements such as #metoo and #timesup to bring redemption to the image of god within women. thankful to get to experience these movements in my lifetime. #2018 #yearofthewoman

text: i won't elaborate on my past. but for decades i felt powerless, i felt that i was stuck with what was. my mother telling me "it's what women like you get in life.."(she was refering to my lack of attractiveness) it took three things in my life to strengthen my back, to force me forward. it was the past year that opened my eyes, woke me up. a year of acceptance(of good and bad) a year of growth, a year of realizing the power in my own hands, within me. two of those things were my daughter's. i -refused- to let them grow up in the world i had. now, i don't want someone out there waiting decades like i did to wake up to their personal power the control of their life, their acceptance of self! even if my (often glitter ridden) post help one person. i will be happy. i want to be the voice i didn't hear in my life! i want people to believe  in themselves!! 🌹💗🌹#selflove #selfcare #selfdiscovery #wellbeing #wellness #jusssayin #settingboundariesandfsu #thetruthturnsmeon #boundaries #nocontact #redflags #narcissist #narcissisticabuse #narcissism #metoo #abuse #crazymaking #emotionalabuse #toxicrelationships #survivor #gaslighting #toxicpeople  #mentalhealthawareness #domesticviolence #believewomen #ifmywoundswerevisible #dontlookback #narcissisticabusesurvivor #witchesofinstagram  #pagansofinstagram

text:
okay, xmas is over, but our wishes keep going :) women still only make $0.80 for every dollar a man makes - but in some states the stats are much more bleak... the pay gap in louisiana for example is widest in the us at 70 cents. but race also plays a big role.. for example, hispanic women only make 54 cent on the dollar compared to white men. what makes this situation even worse is that women are penalized for having a kid (women without kids make around 5% more) whereby men are rewarded (men with kids make almost 20% more then their childless counterpart). we’re just saying... 🙄

today was just one of those days. i've been doing a lot of reflecting and am really preparing myself for an end of year emotional cleanse/shedding where i hope to let go of a lot of internal stuff that is no longer serving me. this work is hard. but it's what makes me stronger and stronger every day. i bawled my eyes out today and once i'd had a good cry, i remembered this quote i'd found yesterday and it was kind of the answer i needed. i know what i need to let go of but yet the residual attachment issues i have from past trauma keeps me stuck longing for what i know just isn't good for me. at a brain level, i know i deserve better. i just need to bring the rest of me on board. what do you guys do to help yourselves really get that you do deserve better? ❤

text:
¡hola, querubines! 👼🏻👼🏼👼🏾
hoy he tenido el placer de estar con algunas integrantes de #elclubdelosviernes, grupo de lectura de el gato de cheshire.
ha sido una experiencia fantástica. hemos hablado de #ohmygothess, que ha sido la novela elegida para diciembre. me encanta charlar de las tramas y los personajes como si de amigos se trataran, así como mezclar risas con reflexiones varias.
me he encontrado un grupo divertido y ecléctico (y cositas ricas en la mesa, ñam ñam 🍪).
me siento muy agradecida por la invitación y la acogida que le han dado a la historia.💜
si sois de zaragoza, os recomiendo pasar por esta preciosa librería repleta de pequeñas joyas y con infusiones de lo más ricas, un rincón traído directamente desde el país de las maravillas. y si os subís al carro de las lecturas conjuntas, no dudéis en sumaros a este club de los viernes, porque el buen rollo está asegurado.
también caí en la tentación y compré un libro, pero esa es otra historia...
ℹ

text:
"algo cruje en nuestro país, y es el patriarcado. todavía tiene fuerza, y sigue ganando espacio en el sentido común machista de gran parte de la sociedad, pero está en crisis, cruje porque se resquebraja. las pibas lo están tirando abajo, todos los días. las actrices, pero también aquellas que no tienen tanta visibilidad y le ponen el cuerpo a una lucha que es de vida o muerte. no banalicemos esta pelea ni pensemos que se le da difusión porque se trata de un problema con nombres propios de artistas reconocidos. el feminismo sigue avanzando contra las estructuras enfermas del partiarcado. hoy quedó, una vez más confirmado. no nos callamos más. mirá cómo nos ponemos." ⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀
they took us away so many things that they ended up taking away our fear. "something is cracking in our country, and it is patriarchy, it still has strength, and continues to gain space in the common sense of a large part of society, but it is in crisis, crunching because it cracks." the girls are throwing it down everyday but also those who do not have much visibility and put their body to a life or death fight. do not banalize this fight or think that it has this diffusion because it is a problem with proper names and recognized artists, feminism continues to advance against the sick structures of partiarchy, today it was once again confirmed, we do not shut up anymore, mirá como nos ponemos"  #revistasudestada #miracomonosponemos #niunamenos #nonoscallamosmas #yositecreo #sevaacaer #metoo

text:
en el 2018 descubrí que, principalmente, somos seres humanos, sin importar nuestra orientación sexual o nuestro género. hallé belleza en cada una de las personas que conocí, estreche amistades sin importar nacionalidad y me encontré amando a quienes me aman.

el 2018 fue un año de luchas, de reivindicación y de protesta, de mujeres que alzaron su voz en contra de quienes las cosificaban, las maltrataban y la reducían, ¡no más!

entendí, en el 2018, que las minorías deben pararse con orgullo, gritar con valentía y mostrar el rostro, ¡nosotros existimos!

halle a muchas personas que están haciendo labores hermosas, comunicando realidades, hablando por quienes no pueden y que desde nuestras pequeñas trincheras podemos impulsar cambios, me hallé más humanos, tratando de ubicar el dolor ajeno, hacerlo mío, compartiéndolo y superándolo.

en el 2018 lloré por extraños, marché con orgullo, hablé por quienes ya no están y le pedí a un estado, firmemente, que dejara de tratarme como ciudadano de segunda, porque ante la ley todos somos iguales.

el 2018 fue un año para aprender y espero que el 2019 me permita seguir aprendiendo y poniéndolo en práctica.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
message from chelsea miller: 
january 25-26, 2019, columbia university will be hosting the third annual her legacy conference and gala. after two days of workshops and panels ranging from "unlocking your leadership potential" to "redefining activism", attendees will end their weekend walking the red carpet at the her legacy gala. the gala will be an evening of live performances, awards, and special guests. tarana burke founder of the #metoo movement and recently named person of the year by time magazine was honored last year. over a dozen media platforms will be covering the weekend. ——————————————————-
tickets start as low as $15 (food included). though centering the voices of women and girls of color, the weekend is open to everyone. (available on eventbrite) - link : https://www.eventbrite.com/e/her-legacy-conference-gala-2019-tickets-53576428540#tickets

text:
i am a recovering perfectionist.

its hard work. my mind still freaks when i feel i didnt measure up, or let someone down or i looked stupid. i panic because i'm afraid of abandonment and rejection. i'm self aware enough to know this about me, yet i still struggle.

i'm learning to calm down and accept the fact i'm not perfect, and i wont do everything right all the time. it's too much pressure to live trying to perform and be perfect in everything. my anxiety goes up, i get back pain and lose my appetite. whew! gonna try and release some of this into the new year.

still a queen 👑✊.
.
.
.

text: the year in illustration 2018. we call on illustrators late at night, in the early morning and on deadline. the subjects are complex: #metoo, the immigration debate, climate change. we ask them to address these topics with sensitivity, wit and feeling — to add fresh perspective and avoid cliché. also, “can you send a sketch in a few hours?” we call on them because, at a time when the news cycle can feel relentless and overwhelming, these images make a different kind of impact: conveying emotion, creating space for thought, adding depth to subjects that may feel at once both too complex and overly familiar. from the thousands of illustrations that appeared in print and online in the new york times this year, here are some of the most notable: the ones that surprised us, that made us feel something, that made us laugh — the ones that made us pause a moment longer than we might have on a busy day in 2018. click the link in our bio for some of the most notable illustrations seen on our pages this year. above, illustrations by @gabalca, @moniiqwa, @armandoveve, @till_lauer. #art #illustration #2018 #images
