text:
"the pit, snakes, scorpions and forgiveness" will be our teaching this sunday for our last gathering of 2018. in order to fully move forward into a new year, we need to learn to find healing of our past, forgive those who have brought us harm and even harder learn to forgive ourselves. sometimes it's easier to extend grace to someone else more than it is to yourself. have you been there? .
.

are you tired of viewing your present and your future through the filter and lens of your past hurt, pain, regret and dissapointments? who is that person you carry around even though they aren't there? what is that thing, that you just can't seem to get past? do you long for the forgiveness of god? there is freedom from unforgiveness, bitterness, resentment, regret, or self hatred. jesus wants to kick down every wall we've built and bring us out into the freedom of wide and open spaces mentally and spiritually. .
.
.
the fringe church | sundays 10am
www.thefringehamilton.com
105 n. 2nd street (ymca)
hamilton, ohio 45011
.

.
.
.
.

text:
do you have a favourite dress that kate has worn? here are my 3 favourite dresses she wore in 2018! all 3 were designed by jenny packham (and one of kate's top go-to designers!)
.
1) kate attended the baftas during the #metoo movement. as a royal, she isn't allowed to make a political statement (the women who attended all wore black) but i think she still respected the movement in choosing a gorgeous dark forest green gown!
.
2) kate rewore a stunning turquoise gown from 2012 to the tusk trust awards, this is my personal favourite dress she has ever worn, aside from her wedding dress!!
.
3) kate donned a pale ice blue gown at the diplomatic corps review, it gave me some frozen/elsa vibes and i thought it was a stunning gown!

the year in illustration 2018. we call on illustrators late at night, in the early morning and on deadline. the subjects are complex: #metoo, the immigration debate, climate change. we ask them to address these topics with sensitivity, wit and feeling — to add fresh perspective and avoid cliché. also, “can you send a sketch in a few hours?” we call on them because, at a time when the news cycle can feel relentless and overwhelming, these images make a different kind of impact: conveying emotion, creating space for thought, adding depth to subjects that may feel at once both too complex and overly familiar. from the thousands of illustrations that appeared in print and online in the new york times this year, here are some of the most notable: the ones that surprised us, that made us feel something, that made us laugh — the ones that made us pause a moment longer than we might have on a busy day in 2018. click the link in our bio for some of the most notable illustrations seen on our pages this year. above, illustrations by @gabalca, @moniiqwa, @armandoveve, @till_lauer. #art #illustration #2018 #images

text: this past year i’ve seen so much pain, loss, depression, loneliness etc. if there’s one thing i learned it’s that people need you in the valleys, to jump in the struggle and tell them they’re not alone. that might be one of the most celebrated things in life; to walk with someone through darkness into light. #mindfulness #awareness #metoo

text:
and some days, you find yourself curled up in a ball on the kitchen floor.
sobbing.
acknowledging the pain.
and releasing it.
this is real life.
it’s not to be glamorized, or judged, or scripted for a 1x1 digital square. i never promised to be anything but myself on this platform. to show you the truest version of me, in all forms. the good, the messy, and the not-so-perfect sides of me.
•
you see, silencing the messy parts of us is an act of isolation. at its core silence is the antithesis of compassion—which is the one thing we need for healing, integrating human connection and creating lasting change in this world.
•
how can we connect when we’re silent? in a time when we’re more “connected” than ever, we’re more isolated than ever—as loneliness has reached “epidemic levels.” according to recent national studies: 1 in 4 americans feel like no one trully knows them & generation z is now the “loneliest generation” in the history of the our country, with 70% feeling like no one knows the real them.
•
part of me didn’t want to share this photo. what will people say, what will people think?
but...
what if...
what if this photo sets people free?
what if this photo gives someone else the permission they’ve been searching for to walk in their imperfect truth?
•
sending love to anyone feeling like they’re going it alone. i promise you, there’s a world that’s desperate for the real you. that’s desperate for your voice. we need it to heal, to connect, to change.
•
we need you—all of the messy-broken-fucked up-beautiful parts of you.

text:
#washington: the trump administration announced on friday a plan designed to make it easier for coal-fired power plants, after nearly a decade of restrictions, to once again release into the atmosphere mercury and other pollutants linked to developmental disorders and respiratory illnesses.

the limits on mercury, set in 2011, were the first federal standards to restrict some of the most hazardous pollutants emitted by coal plants and were considered one of former president barack obama’s signature environmental achievements. since then, scientists have said, mercury pollution from power plants has declined more than 80 percent nationwide.

president trump’s new proposal does not repeal the regulation, known as the mercury and air toxics standards, but it would lay the groundwork for doing so by weakening a key legal justification for the measure. the long-term impact would be significant: it would weaken the ability of the e.p.a. to impose new regulations in the future by adjusting the way the agency measures the benefits of curbing pollutants, giving less weight to the potential health gains.”

text:
#romjulroar day 3: in 2017 i spoke publicly about me rape for the first time. i was terrified. then, nothing bad happened. then, other women shared their experiences with me. •
my vulnerability doesn't make me weak. it belies the strength required to survive. if some perceive me as less-than, or think i should keep it to myself, that's on them. my trauma is not laundry to be washed or luggage to carry. it's part of my experience and enhances my ability to empathize with, and in turn serve, others.
•
imma serve by leading, and by sharing my vulnerability moarrrrrr in 2019.
•
#coachedandloved #coachmk #metoo #survivor #speakup #rapesurvivor #abusesurvivor #beyondrunning

text:
celebrating screen star tayo sobola

multi talented actress, model, video vixen, presenter and producer. toya sobola  aka sotayo gaga was definitely born for the cameras.

although known in the yoruba film industry, the graduate of sociology from olabisi onabanjo university, ogun state started out featuring in english language movies.

the actress who has featured in many movies including: idakeji ife, egan, corper jide, bella, arewa onijogbon and others is known for the film, arewa onijogbon (2012). sobola attended olabisi onabanjo university where she bagged  a degree in public administration and a diploma in law from lagos state university.

the actress is said to have a multi million naira production studio.

in 2015, she won city people’s entertainment awards for best new yoruba actress of the year and was nominated in another category for most promising actress of the year.

happy 33rd birthday sotayo gaga!

text:
a bishop sent me a message saying l should stop taking about sexual violence since god has helped me,now l am married(in his words) he went as far as advising me  not to bring shame on the man who married me. in his words the man did me a great favor. 
this is my response, sir with all due respect l will not stop talking. i will continue to lend my voice ,l will continue to speak out  against rape ,molestation,incest or any form of sexual violence until something is done. i am a christian girl who is not ashamed to speak out. 
our dear ochanya died after being violated sexually for years by father and son 😭😭 and some people still think talking about this does not make sense? how many more innocent children will die before we know there is an emergency? most sexual violence cases are perpetrated by people the victims know. because of society's shame,stigma and judgement most survivors never speak. the number of survivors who have spoken is nothing compared to the ones who have never spoken about their abuse. we will not keep quiet. 
sexual violence can have harmful and lasting consequences for the victims,families, communities.  sexual violence victimisation is associated with several health risk behaviour. the effects can have psychological,emotional,and physical effects on a survivor. the effects are not easy to deal,it can take a life time to heal. with the right help and support survivors can be managed.

sexual violence is not a joke,it should never be trivialised.  we will not be silenced. our voice,our power.... to everyone who has survived, l salute you big time. i salute your courage. i salute your strength. we survived the abuse,we will definitely survive the recovery . our lives matter. 
#metoomovement #metoo #notoviolenceagainstwomen #nigerianfeminist #irememberabuse #unmutted #awakening

ラーレ・イスタンブール (lale istanbul)は、トルコ製のインテリアやファッションアクセサリーを中心にセレクトしたアイテムをご紹介しております。.
.
＊「ラーレ・イスタンブール」について...
.
ラーレ (lale) とは...
トルコ語で「チューリップ」の意味。(先の尖ったトルコ原産のチューリップはトルコ伝統織物やセラミックのモチーフに愛用者されています。)
.
イスタンブール (istanbul) とは...
「コンスタンティノープル」の別名を有し、東洋と西洋が交差するトルコの古都。
.
ラーレ・イスタンブール 公式ブランドサイト
www.laleistanbul.com
.

continuation of the last post: he starts kissing my neck, biting it... and i didn't know what to do. i was literally shocked. i didn't know what to do, how to react, i... i just stood there 😞 i couldn't see my friend anywhere either... then he stopped and went to dance somewhere else. i sighed, relieved that it was over, but then he came back again trying to get me to dance with him and when i said i didn't feel like it he sat me down and started kissing me again... i tried getting him off me by pushing him gently but he wouldn't move... then he started getting to touch-y, i felt his hands on my back, on my hips, on my arms, on my face, on my lips, until he started going a little bit down... when i felt him placing his hand between my legs i "snapped"... i started pulling  him off harder this time, telling "no, fr i don't want this" but he wouldn't move! the thing is, my friends see me as "tough" person, but i am not like that at all! i'm not very good at talking to people, i get nervous every time i need to order my own food, i even hesitate when i want to ask for ketchup, because that required social interaction makes me nervous and i'm afraid that people won't like me... so maybe i should have been more persistent, push him harder, be more acertive when i told him to stop, say it louder, get up and go somewhere else... but i didn't 😞... i don't know why but... i didn't... i just froze... 😓 he didn't touch me *there* again, i guess he wasn't that drunk and understood that part, but he wouldn't get off me. there was a body guard near me but the music was too loud so i couldn't call him, he was too far for me too reach him discreetly, and drank too much to be aware of what was happening to me right under his eyes... my friend eventually showed up and came near us but he must have been as drunk as the guy because he didn't notice me struggling to get him off me. •

text: i know i usually only post my photos, but now, i needed to bring attention to this. pls share this everywhere so it becomes known. we fight for equality everyday, we strive for it. how can we achieve equality if we remove any of the past steps we have taken to move forward. #metoo is not a trend, it’s reality being brought forward into the publics eye. it is no longer a taboo topic. it is one we need to talk about and acknowledge. how are we supposed to have change we even our government is ignoring our pleas? share this. make it known. tag me so i can see our progress. don’t stand by and let us rewind our time. it is almost 2019 don’t let us all fall back to violence being expected and accepted. don’t let bigotry come from those who are supposed to be respected. speak up! no matter who you are or how little you think your voice is, speak up!!!

text:
"the pit, snakes, scorpions and forgiveness" will be our teaching this sunday for our last gathering of 2018. in order to fully move forward into a new year, we need to learn to find healing of our past, forgive those who have brought us harm and even harder learn to forgive ourselves. sometimes it's easier to extend grace to someone else more than it is to yourself. have you been there? .
.

are you tired of viewing your present and your future through the filter and lens of your past hurt, pain, regret and dissapointments? who is that person you carry around even though they aren't there? what is that thing, that you just can't seem to get past? do you long for the forgiveness of god? there is freedom from unforgiveness, bitterness, resentment, regret, or self hatred. jesus wants to kick down every wall we've built and bring us out into the freedom of wide and open spaces mentally and spiritually. .
.
.
the fringe church | sundays 10am
www.thefringehamilton.com
105 n. 2nd street (ymca)
hamilton, ohio 45011
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

you’d be forgiven for feeling like 2018 was a bit of a blur; a lot has happened over the past 12 months, so to help gain some clarity, we’ll be revisiting moments that had an impact on our world. let’s start with the @timesupnow protest at the golden globes, where 300 women turned up in black to protest sexual harassment in us workplaces. the campaign was launched as a companion to the #metoo movement and has raised more than $20m in legal defence funds primarily used to fight sexual misconduct cases brought by low-paid workers. the fund's co-founder, roberta kaplan, said the movement as a whole is encouraging thousands of women to “come out” as victims of misconduct. “i think it’s revolutionary and it’s not going to go back. i can’t see women agreeing to return to the days of isolation and shame.” #thiswas2018

text:
there can be an unspoken conspiracy in community-i certainly used to be a part of this and it goes something like this-
let’s not demand much of ourselves.  or each other.  or of life.  and when it doesn’t go the way we want to to, let’s complain about it and everyone else.  for months. 
there’s another option 
if i am like the 5 people i spend the most time with, i’m very careful of who i allow into my life. 
what am i up to?
what are they up to?
what am i healing?
what are they healing?
do i have a mentor i trust?
do they?
if i start to go off course are these the people i trust to tell me i’m off?
are these the people i want to celebrate with?

for the first time in my life those around me are absolutely those people.  and it all started with an intention for this year of “a community that is loving, nurturing and free”

because when we heal we heal generations before and after us, as well as the ripple affect around us. 
who are your people? 
what are your intentions for 2019?

if you need some help with intentions, are ready to heal and ignite the fire, let’s talk.  let’s heal this one friend group at a time 😊❤️🌈💗💕🎄

text:
i fell in love with this character. this was the most emotional, and darkest song i’ve ever had to sing in front of an audience. emotions took over for most of the performance, but it was honest so i guess that works! i felt very privileged to be a part of this reading and get a taste of playing a very complex character. i look forward to working on it again some day, and bringing this crazy- yet layered sex therapist back to life . #metoo *****no one tells you from the naked truth musical by ian connor and adam j rineer. presented at the greenroom 42, nyc. featuring: katy geraghty, morgan reilly, phil sloves, cheeyang ng, samara ariel ehrlich, gina bilardi, jacen ziev, kathryn francisco
lamont walker ii, nicole loewenstein. music directed by adam j rineer. directed by ian connor. stage managed by emily todt. patrick tice-carroll (keys 2)
chris mcwilliams(drums), zach sicherman (bass), juan esteban arango (guitar) @nakedtruthmusical www.nakedtruthmusical.com*****

text: summerar 2018 med mina 9 mest gillade bilder här på instagram. jag kan snabbt konstatera att både år och bilder börjar och avslutas i afrika. på två helt olika platser. den första till zanzibar över nyår var en rehabiliteringsresa efter år av lite för högt arbetstempo och jag behövde en rejäl handbroms från allt. hem igen till bästa nikki som håller mig varm i alla väder (ja, hon får sova i sängen). en start på året som även innebar att emmas ptgym blev @ptgymmet ihop med @annikawinterros något som glädjer mig enormt. inte bara att expandera för egen del utan även att hitta en partner och kollega samt att märka hur behovet av personlig träning ökar i sandviken med omnejd från min start 2012. under året spenderade jag en del tid i bilen, först upp till @friskgymnasten i hudiksvall för privatlektioner inför höstens utbildning på @asperaeducation. målet var att certifiera mig till aspera movement integrator, vilket jag gjorde i december. nu kan jag hjälpa mina kunder till än bättre resultat med detta sätt att tänka genom bland annat rörelseintegrering. jag blev nominerad till årets företagare 2018 i sandvikens kommun vilket var otroligt hedersamt. under året tog jag även ett beslut om att bara sponsra damidrott vilket jag är mycket stolt över. som en av de större sponsorerna i @sandvikensif närvarade jag även under klubbens 100 årsfirande med galaglans. det påminner mig vidare om att de två böcker jag hunnit med att läsa under året båda är skrivna av @oloflundh. det känns bra att vara påläst inom idrottsrörelsen även om hela min idé om att bara sponsra damidrott är sprungen ur #metoo. så julen 2018 i nigeria med mycket kärlek och omtanke men också extrem fattigdom och ett land där det skulle behövas en greta thunberg. tack 2018 🙏🏽

text:
this year saw the highest estimated turnout for midterms in more than 100 years. there were a bunch of positive firsts, like the first muslim women and first native american women elected to congress, the first openly gay man elected as governor, among others. more congresswomen were elected than ever before. but florida still doesn’t understand elections.
🤦‍♂️ then there was brett kavanaugh, president @realdonaldtrump’s second addition to the supreme court after justice kennedy put in his notice. kavanaugh was accused by professor dr. christine blasey ford of sexually assaulting her decades ago. other women came forward with stories, too. kavanaugh denies them all. there were hearings. and protests. and lots and lots of opinions. some thought he deserved the benefit of the doubt. others felt we should #believewomen. a lot of people were reminded of anita hill. nonetheless, kavanaugh got the job.

text:
todos os anos, o departamento da universidade de oxford destaca a palavra do ano pra língua inglesa. a ideia é representar o clima e os conceitos do ano em uma palavra e sugerir uma reflexão sobre ela. em 2013, por exemplo, a palavra foi selfie. em 2016, pós-verdade e ano passado foi um termo que celebra as mudanças políticas, sociais e culturais promovidas pelas atitudes dos jovens, youthquake.

e em 2018, a palavra foi... tóxico.
a gente não tem dúvida que ela contempla demais o ano que passou e é fundamental que nós, juntos, possamos refletir sobre e tomar atitudes pra que ela não faça parte do nosso 2019. não com tanta força. nós exercemos o tóxico nas nossas relações pessoais e materiais, na nossa alimentação e, claro, com o meio ambiente. o nexo contou que a palavra também abraça o movimento #metoo, protagonizado pelas mulheres contra o assédio de homens que insistem na masculinidade tóxica. a ideia, a princípio, era escolher essa dupla de palavras como a premiada de 2018, mas o grupo entendeu que estamos nos relacionando de forma tóxica com tudo, especialmente com o planeta.

a nossa postura a respeito da alimentação com agrotóxicos, nossa relação de consumo desenfreado em uma sociedade tóxica, em que ter likes e ter o look da semana é o mais importante do que a conexão com as pessoas, o nosso consumo massivo de plásticos descartáveis, tóxicos, ignorando o nosso impacto nocivo pro planeta e pros animais. nossa postura tóxica diante de tantas situações tóxicas sem tomar qualquer atitude... somos uma sociedade intoxicada.

e é triste reconhecer a escolha certeira da universidade de oxford pra 2018.

mas levanta a cabeça! esse é um sintoma, mas que tem muita cura com mais amor, mais gentileza, mais comunidade. vamos juntos mudar esse panorama pra 2019.

afinal, temos um mundo pra transformar. 🙂

"se eu deixo a dorminhoca bunda rica da mamãe no colo, se coloco na cama, se levo pra passear todo final de tarde... é porque a mãe sou eu. se amamento deitada, se não cortei minha unha, se só deixo de fralda ou muito coberta... é porque a mãe sou eu. se viajei com menos de dois meses, se pra todo lugar que vou eu levo, se ainda uso luva, se comprei muitas roupas, sapatos, produtos de higiene ou sou a louca da giovana baby... é porque a mãe sou eu. se não deixo chorar, se evito alimentos com medo de cólicas, ou se como algo que dizem que não pode... é porque a mãe sou eu. se já uso hidratantes e parfum, ou deixo usar meu peito de chupeta... é porque a mãe sou eu...nenhuma mãe faz algo que faça mal ao seu filho, se fazemos é porque tá dando certo. pode ser realmente que tenha dado errado pra alguma outra criança, mas toda mãe tem um instinto fora do normal para suprir suas necessidades dentro do que precisa. por aqui, algo que parece besteira eu tenho medo, e algo mais sério, eu me sinto segura, e sempre dá certo. confie no seu instinto, faça conforme seu conforto e haja com seu coração. a mãe é você !!!"

text:
esta abuela me acaba de dar una idea 😁prefiero mil veces dar mi trabajo y mis sacrificios a una protectora de animales que dejarle a los hipócritas algo... así que @bbva @_bbvaworld_  ya le diré a mi gestor de sucursal que protectora de #tenerife ponerle mis pertenencias 😎
-
estoy cansada que me digan: me prestas bibi .... mejor dime, me regalas y ya veo si te lo doy 🤬 pero que me tomen el pelo me jode!!. solo una persona de tenerife (de los que me conocen) nunca me pidió nada y el sabe todo de mi, lo que tengo y lo que no... así que mucha gente debería de lavarse la boca con lejía! para hablar del padre de mi “hijo” ... el no es perfecto y lo conozco mejor que nadie! pero lo que no es un sinvergüenza! y un cara dura, más bien cuando era una cría me ayudó... no permito que nadie! me hable mal de él y la opinión de las personas ignorantes y envidiosas no me interesa. después algunos vais a el hablarle mal de mi, como si el no supiera quién soy ya. ¡no tengo! nada que demostrar.
-
pd: el que quiera dinero que se coja un avión para #noruega con (@flynorwegian unos 50€), le puedo guiar dónde están las instituciones públicas, la embajada española etc... hay muchos macdonald y apartamentos para limpiar... pero que se deje de llorar en la playa que los inmigrantes que llevamos 12 años fuera de las islas y estamos regresando no nos hemos sacado la lotería, llevamos años pasando frío y trabajando duro!.
-
el que algo quiere algo le cuesta. ¡trabajar!

text:
**giveaway is now closed** this #badassquilt was designed by berene campbell of @happysewlucky in response to the #metoo movement, and to celebrate women for their amazing strengths.  this month it made the quiltcon cut and is now on it’s way to nashville. whoohoo! and so, of course, we needed pins to add a little extra badass into the mix. they will ship in feb but are available for pre-order at @pinkdoorfabrics (and a limited number will be for sale in their booth at quiltcon) the badass quilt pattern is available on etsy in @happysewlucky’s shop, and comes with the full #vintagealphabetpattern, including punctuation. ...but for now let’s party a little. 🎉who is up for a giveaway then?! we are giving away a full pattern, and pair of both badass and brave pins to you and a friend. here’s how to enter: 1. you must follow both @pinkdoorfabrics and @happysewlucky.  2. like this post.  3.tag a quilty friend who you think is badass. you may tag as many times as you like on both posts for more chances to win. 
rules: giveaway ends at 9pm pst on sunday dec 30. a winner will be chosen at random, and winner will be dm'd on monday. if we don’t hear back within 24 hours, we will pick another winner. badass quilt pattern will be emailed to the winner and person they tagged. pins will ship by mail in february. offer open worldwide, but you must have an open profile so that we can see that you are a quilter, not a spambot. no purchase necessary. this giveaway is in no way associated with, or endorsed by instagram.

_
would you treat a #dog this way?
_
dairy’s dark secret
the typical dairy cow on a farm produces nearly 22,000 pounds of milk a year – more than double­ what its forebears did 40 years ago. they never graze; their hooves have rotted from standing in their own filth. 
_
cows, like pigs, are social creatures; their babies are even more so. they nuzzle strangers, groan with pleasure when you pet them, and attach without complaint to callous minders. their sweetness gets them nowhere at auctions or at farms, however; the men and women working here smack them with boards and kick them in the haunches to move them forward. as one undercover investigator stated; “so common,” “seen guys punch them, stick cattle prods in their eyes, bragging, ‘i totally got her in the eyeball!’ it’s what happens when you do this long enough. they’re not your fellow creatures, they’re just trouble.
_
then there's the baby...a calf that can’t get up. its velveteen eyes are wet but blank; he barely stirs when jostled by other calves. “he got sick and gave up,” and so it goes with farmers who gave up farming to become cruel jailers of their "stock". it’s like they hate their own animals for having feelings.”
_
how can you possibly justify this for a glass of milk, a piece of cheese, a bowl of #icecream?there are so many plant-based alternatives available. please choose wisely. will your choices be responsible for creating more victims?
_

text:
kwanzaa  day 3: ujima (collective work and responsibility) to build and maintain our community together and make our brothers' and sisters' problems our problems, and to solve them together.

scriptures for reflection:
nehemiah 2:17-18 (nrsv)
1 corinthians 12:21-25 (nrsv)

if the first principle dealt with the concept of unity, then the third one expands the conversation to include work and responsibility, not as individuals but as a collective. given the state of our communities, we should take this moment to realize that like the people of israel during nehemiah's time we must not only fight off external threats, we must also work internally to increase our strength. to give this a concrete example, we need to be vigilant about fighting for justice and restoration for those impacted by the #metoo movement just as we are about the  #blacklivesmatter movement. we need to fight for the rights of black people against white supremacy as well as challenge ourselves to not repeat the behaviors of our oppressors when it comes to up holding patriarchal systems or denying the rights and humanity of our lgbtq family. it really is either we all get free or nobody is free... and the freedom takes work, it's not cheap and it requires all of us to do our part, in our lanes as god has called us to do. 
ujima also reminds us not to get so caught up in our roles and statues. the late prophet frantz fanon once spoke to this in his book "wretched of the earth" when he said "for when the troops come we will either all be saved or all be captured; in such a context, the "every man for himself concept, the atheist's form of salvation, is prohibited.*" your titles, statuses, class affiliation etc won't save you. it may offer some small privilege but it will not save you. we truly are in this fight together. this is bore out in the scripture from 1 corinthians. all parts of the body make up the whole and when working together, so much more is achieved. no part is greater than the whole and it is all of our responsibility to fight the good fight in whatever venue or role we can. 
can we work together so we can all be free? 
pastor t

text:
i’m not a man but i love the #polishedman movement. it encourages men to paint one of their fingernails for a week to represent the 1 in 5 children who will be the victims of sexual violence in their lifetime. please join the movement and spread the word. education is the impetus for change 💙. .
.
it all began when ygap's elliot costello of australia visited cambodia for a project with hagar international. there he met a girl named thea who had been abused. they painted their nails together and he promised her he'd always have one of his painted to remember her. .
.
that one promise has turned into a movement as more guys become a #polishedman to stand up against sexual violence against kids. according to its website, "being a polished man means challenging violent behavior and language, both locally and globally."
.
with 96 percent of the this violence perpetrated by men, the initiative is calling on them to be the voice of change. #vaginasunitedvu #ourdaughtersarewatching #yourvoicematters #metootimesup #metoo #timesup #believesurvivors #metoomovement #endrape #rapeculture #womensmarch #believewomen #keepfighting #truth #metoostories #abuseawareness #endrapeoncampus #enoughisenough #whyididntreport #yourvoicematters #metooisvu #familyviolence #itsnothyourfault #womenunited #womenpower #womenempowerment #womenpowerment

text:
на днях со старшим сыном сходили на новогодний мультфильм «гринч». это красочная и добрая история про зеленого человечка, которые живет в пещере на вершине горы вдали от всех. он злой и угрюмый. а звуки новогодних песен, и радостные вопли, доносящиеся из города, выводят его из душевного равновесия. и он решается испортить всем жителем праздник.

мы получили большое удовольствие от этого мультика😉посмеялись над забавными шутками и растрогались в конце) рекомендую к просмотру деткам с 6 лет. поднятие новогоднего настроения будет обеспечено👍🏼🎅🏻🎄
⠀ 
а вы успеваете с новогодней суете посещать кинотеатры?

text: how entrenched patriarchy is making women pay for demanding safer workplace #metoomovement #metoo❤️ #metoo may have come as a storm, in two distinct and momentous bursts that broke upon india, but it’s obviously not a simple “moment” that has passed, leaving everyone to cope with the next headline event. something as complex as this stays in the bloodstream of society, changing behaviour, subtly altering the atmosphere, exerting its influence in various ways, not all of it savoury. two months since a band of women spoke out against the inappropriate conduct of men, calling them out in public, often with evidence, there even seems to be a reverse wave—of silent reprisals.

text: jordan is a six-year-old boy who loves basketball, dancing and superheroes. jordan came to the new york center for children after he disclosed that his uncle sexually abused him. when jordan began therapy at nycc, he suffered from severe trauma. he often cried, had tantrums, reported daily nightmares and flashbacks. through the power of play therapy and the use of superheroes, jordan was able to talk about the abuse he experienced in a safe space. therapy helped jordan make sense of his abuse and begin healing. for jordan, therapy has been an incredible gift. this holiday season, we invite you to give a child who has experienced abuse a gift that will last a lifetime: the gift of therapy. to donate, read more about jordan and how your support can help children like him heal and succeed, please visit the link on bio. 🎁 💝

text:
pour une fois je voulais évoquer un sujet sérieux dans un post public . alors j’ai longuement hésité mais j’ai déjà largement évoqué l’homophobie donc là maintenant je voulais parler d’agressions sexuelles . pourquoi maintenant un sujet si sérieux ? (je parle on dirait un prof c’est assez impressionnant.) parce que je me suis rendue compte qu’on se confie mieux quand on ne sait pas qui nous écoute . comme pleins de gens j’ai du mal à me confier et quand je le fais je suis pas à l’aise . alors je le dis ici. j’ai vécu des agressions sexuelles . a plusieurs reprises . exhibitionnisme , viol , chantage sexuel . et grâce à ma chérie @kellyannewilkins j’ai envie d’en parler parce que c’est pas une honte . parce que même si ça avance tout le monde se tait et que c’est tabou . je suis une gosse , je parle de manière trop crue et je vous encourage à faire pareil . parce que plus on se tait , plus se sera banalisé . j’ai eu la chance de pas en garder de traumatismes contrairement à beaucoup d’autres qui on sombré dans la dépression , qui se sont renfermées et qui ne supportent plus le contact physique . je n’en ai rien gardé tout simplement parce que ma maladie m’empêche d’être actrice de ma propre vie . j’ai l’impression de constamment me mentir à moi même et de ne pas vivre ma vie . en le disant en public je me rend compte que c’est réel . et que mon inconscient s’en souvient. #metoo 
assez étrange comme post mais la parole au final c’est le début de la guérison.

text:
this canada wide anti-sexual violence in the restaurant industry donation page has reached significant amounts and it’s worth noticing because it’s just going to get bigger.  the movement is growing and will spread over the next months to hold more people accountable as well as supporting the causes and organizations that support victims of sexual violence.  donate today to help them reach their goals and stay tuned for more coming soon. 
this fundraiser (https://fundly.com/hospitality-industry-standing-with-survivors) is endorsed by members of the food and wine industries in toronto/prince edward county, as well as a number of canadian celebrity food personalities like jen agg, matty matheson, joe beef, ivy knight. 
the fundraiser was started after the survivor accounts  of rape and sexual violence were revealed about norman hardie who is the founder and operator of norman hardie wines.  i am in constant contact with victims and with the organizers of this fundraiser to help anyway i can.  it would be amazing if some ottawa restaurant owners and businesses came onboard to help with the cause.  the #metoo movement is becoming a real thing now and you won’t be able to ignore it.  do not end up in the cross hairs when people start questioning your silence when it comes to addressing sexual misbehaviour in the food world.  follow for more info and support -> @dandelioninitiative @mmmarywood 
also tagging the following organizations and people who have been working on similar initiatives in ottawa -> @octevaw @sascottawa @baileyreid85 @badandbitchypod #ordersup #metoo #timesup

text:
2018 год в instagram: всё самое лучшее и интересное
⠀
лучшие стикеры и маски, самые часто используемые эмодзи и хэштеги. instagram с радостью замечает, что пользователи делятся радостью и любовью. и вот почему.
⠀
самой часто используемой гифкой в сториз стало инстаграмное сердечко
⠀
самой полюбившейся маской стали «влюблённые глазки» (heart eyes)
⠀
эмодзи сердце было использовано за 2018 год аж четырнадцать миллиардов раз
⠀
а самым счастливым местом на земле был назван токийский диснейленд. именно к фото из этой локации чаще всего использовали больше всего улыбающихся смайликов
⠀
самое большое сообщество 2018 года — асмр. это видео, которые почему-то доставляют удовольствие
⠀
самым быстрорастущим хэштегом стал #fortnite. неудивительно, ведь это самая популярная компьютерная игра в мире
⠀
не обошлось и без корейских музыкантов. аккаунт с названием @bts.bighitofficial стало самым большим фанатским сообществом
⠀
самым крутым (большим) танцевальным флешмобом стал #inmyfeelingschallenge
⠀
при этом instagram — место не только для развлечений
в 2018 году были популярными хештеги-лозунги против сексуального насилия над женщинами: #metoo (полтора миллиона), #timesup (597 тысяч), #marchforourlives (562 тысячи)
⠀
а что в инстаграм запомнилось больше всего вам?
⠀
например, за 2018 год в нашем инстаграме стало более 60 тысяч подписчиков. присоединяйтесь @likeyou_io!
⠀
#развлечения #instagram #итоги

text: 2018 had the highest highs. (legit one if my best years ever.) and it marked the year that i was raped for the 6th time. didn't realize how healing this journey of health has been for all aspects of my life. reading "not that bad" edited by roxane gay and the "grown-woman theology" chapter of "eloquent rage" by brittany c. cooper broke me and built me up. advocating for myself in all ways taught me how to love myself. taking care of my body forced me to confront my fat shaming ways and internalized guilt of the pain my body held. my life looks very different than it did last year. i own my body and sexuality in a way i haven't before. require my partners to attend to my needs fully or bounce. use lingerie as a tool of healing and liberation. am i grateful for my rape? fuck no. am i reframing what the event meant in my life? abso-fucking-lutely. #metoo #bralettesasshirtsforeva #selfcareerryday

text_retweet:
continuing our international #repost streak, we thank  @danilo.superbidasilva for today's share. 🇧🇷 ・・・. o que está por trás do sucesso de grandes empresas, movimentos sociais e personalidades tão diversas?
as regras de influência costumavam ser claras: o poder - fora do alcance da maioria - era um objetivo a ser conquistado e um bem a ser protegido. essa definição, no entanto, está com os dias contados. se antes eram poucos os que decidiam o futuro da sociedade, a era da conectividade possibilitou o surgimento de um tipo diferente de poder.
em “o novo poder”, @henrytimms e @jeremyheimans traçam um panorama de casos emblemáticos do mundo dos negócios, da política e da cultura pop - de movimentos como #metoo e o crescimento de megaplataformas, passando pelas inesperadas vitórias de obama e trump, até a propagação das ações do estado islâmico - em que lideranças disseminadas, plataformas colaborativas e redes sociais chacoalharam a velha ordem mundial.
longe de uma batalha entre o “bem” e o “mal”, na disputa entre novo e velho poder o leitor descobre o que os dois lados têm a oferecer para aqueles que desejam moldar o futuro.
#liderança #lideranca #leadership #onovopoder #newpower #internet #hyperconnectedworld

heads held high, survivors! get ready to smash those pearls (unless they were gifted) or put on that pantsuit!

we're entering 2019 unashamed and with rejuvenated spirits and the strength to impact massive change. it's time we started using our powerful voices to speak out against sexual violence and abuse. 
in a world where 1 in 4 (probably more like 1 in 3) will experience some variation of sexual violence/abuse/assault, it's important that we fight as hard as we can to protect each other.

personally, i'm dedicating this year to learning how to change society's view of sexual violence/abuse, teaching prevention, supporting other survivors, partnering with other survivor communities, and being more bold in my advocacy. 
what are you going to do this year to help fight sexual violence? share in the comments or give helpful suggestions to other readers!

text:
i once wanted to take a road trip to the cabins in tennessee with a black chick. i planned to do some fishing and hunting. i vet women this way if i view them as relationship material. obviously this is before i was mgtow. i vet them on quite a few things but these are common ones.

1. her ability to get down and dirty in nature without complaining. use her hands, fish effectively, clean the fish. kick her shoes off and get dirty.

2. put her on the motorcycle with me and ride like hell is chasing me. i expect her to freak out but i want to gauge her reaction, because it's a direct correlation of her trust for me. getting out of her comfort zone is a sign of trust.

3. i grab the rifle go to a hunting cabin and test her marksmenship skills. if road trip isn't feasible go to the gun range.

it was a vacation/shit-test/evaluation to see if she was worth investing in. this is to see if she is able to live off the land and survive in nature for when the shtf.

this chick told me, can we fly there instead cuz i already did the whole road trip thing plenty of times with my ex. so before i could even make the trip to vet her she eliminated herself.

if a woman has done something or been somewhere with a previous guy, it would behoove of her to accept the opportunity because every new person brings about a new experience.

lmagine a chick doesn't want to go to amsterdam anymore because she has been many times with an ex. if you're a man that has always wanted to go to amsterdam and the chick you love doesn't want to share the moment with you, how would you feel?

men like to make their women happy. like when you get your kids a toy they always wanted, to see the joy in their face. so imagine getting a kid the same gift 10 years in a row, they won't have the same joy as the first time.

a mgtow tuber wanted to buy a home with his fiance. she said let's just move into my place. they both had homes but he wanted to create new memories, she was already attached to her home.

one very common one is when a man marries a single mother. since she already has kids she may tell him she doesn't want more, denying him the opportunity to create his legacy through a woman he loves.

هنر ايران آلوده است
.
در مورد بحث فساد در سينما همين بس كه با يك فاجعه مواجه هستيم.بيش از دو دهه سينماى ما به جايي رسيده كه با طيب خاطر ميگويم"صد رحمت به سينماى زمان شاه"دست كم بحث شايسته سالارى رعايت ميشد.امثال صدف طاهريان كه به لطف دوست پسر عزيزش آقاى.....،،،،بازيگر شد،كمترين سوژه معرف حضور است.البته ايشان مظلوم نمايي فرمودن.
.
آقايان و خانم هاى اهالى سينما و تئاتر و موسيقى،سر خود را زير برف نكنيد.سكوت يعنى همراهى با اين جنايت.ما هم نياز به يك جنبش #metoo 
داريم.آزار جنسى و سو استفاده مالى از هنرمندان بس است.خانم و آقا هم ندارد
.
هر فردى با هر هنرى،خاطره اى از جنس اخاذى،پرداخت رشوه،باج خواهى،پيشنهاد جنسى و.....دارد در پايين همين پست منتشر كند.لطفا دوستان هنرمندتان و هنرمندان را پايين پست تگ كنيد.
.
اين يك بيانيه حق طلبانه است و هدفش روشنگرى و آگاهى بخشى است
.دوستان نازنينم با شناختى كه از شما دو عزيز دارم ميدانم كه بسيار هنرمند و با اخلاق هستيد.وظيفه ماست كه از شما و هنرنابتان حمايت كنيم.با همه وجود غمگينم كه هنر سرزمين ما در چنگ مشتى بى هنر هوس باز اسير است.آرزو ميكنم به حقتان برسيد

text:
truth 😳🤯😐 raw moment..... 👋🏼🙌🏼 i have grown a lot in this last year and done a lot of self reflecting, counseling and self development but i am ready to embark on this new journey of mine that i will be sharing with you all soon. this journey might cost me relationships, people and things but i am so ready because my body deserves it and i owe it to myself and my family. 
to love yourself is not easy, i’ve been through some horrible things in my childhood as well as my adulthood that haunt me to this day still and  for many years i have numbed the pain in so many ways and lashed out in anger 😡 and tears 😭, and i am realizing all these years i’ve just been in a lot of pain 😞 . it’s time to stop numbing the pain when the only true way to get through the pain and the hurt is to truly feel it and be present. i know some growing pains are coming, but i am ready because there is no growth in your comfort zone. 
#metoo #workinprogress #staytuned #newme 
happy friday 🌸🙏🏼 .
.
.
.
.
.
#growth #change #godsplan #loveyourself #pain #suffering #numbness #life #struggles #timeforchange #itstime

100 كبسولة

الثوم والزعتر مادتان مضادتان للتأكسد ممزوجتان معاً كسلاح فعال للحصول على صحة جيدة عندما يقطع الثوم أو يهرس فإنها الأنزيمات التي تعمل على إيجاد مادة قوية قاتلة للبكتيريا (دون ذكر الخصائص الفعالة في الثوم حيث أظهرت الدراسات بأنه يساعد على تنظيم الكولسترول وعلى تحويل المواد الدهنية إلى طاقة وتساعد على حماية الجسم من التجاعيد

مكونات الثوم و الزعتر من فوريفير
زيت الثوم المركز  زعـتـر :50ملغ من الورق المسحوق

ما هو الثوم وما فوائد عناصره الداخله في تركيبة منتج فوريفر؟

الثوم نبتة مركبة مكونه الأساسي هو مادة الأليسين عند قطع أو سحق الثوم تتفاعل الأليسين مع خميرة الأليناز المنتجة للأليسين والمتواجدة أيضاً في الثوم وهذا ما يعطي الثوم رائحته المميزة الحادَّة.
الأليسين عنصر مقاوم للبكتيريا يدخل مجرى الدم ويطهر الرئتين والأمعاء وينقي البشرة.
الأجوين هو عنصر مضاد لتخثر الدم.
اللستين يساعد على غزالة الدهون المخزنة كالكلسترول وتحويل الدهون إلى طاقة.
مركبات سلفور الثوم المضادة للفطريات يجعلها علاجاً لمختلف المشاكل الصحية بما فيها الأنفلونزا مثلاً. ما هي فوائد عناصر الزعتر الداخله في تركيبة منتج فوريفر؟
الزعتر يحتوي على حمض التنيك حمض الكربوليك وثيمول أي زيت الزعتر 
وتساعد في معالجة النزلة الرئوية وفي تهدئة الجهاز الهضمي وهذه المكونات تعمل كمضاد للبكتيريا والفطريات.  طريقة الاستعمال:
قرص واحد مع كل وجبة

جل الألوفيرا من فوريفر  هو مستقر ومحفوظ بعملية طبيعية وهذه الطريقة مسجلة باسم فوريفر بما يحفظ خواصه الصحية دون تغيير ولذلك فهو مفضل بواسطة الذين يسعون للمحافظة على جهاز هضمي سليم ومعافى ويتوقون لرفع طاقة أجسامهم 
ويعتبر جل الألوفيرامن أفضل  المغذيات إذا واظب الانسان على استخدامه بانتظام له العديد من الاستخدامات ينظم ضغط الدم ويعالج مشاكل الجهاز الهضمي القرحه والقالون وغيرها •  حجم العبوة : 1 لتر

text:
5 years ago i got this tattoo.  at the time it was 6 months since i had been raped.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i was holding my breath waiting for january 1 to come. i wanted to be in a new year where i hadn't been raped. when i could say it happened "last year" and not "earlier this year."⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i wanted to be out of 2013 as fast as possible.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
but, i also wanted a mindset to take with me on my journey into the future as i continued to pursue healing.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
this tattoo is a reminder of hope in the promise that light always conquers darkness, and a reminder to walk alongside others to help them in their journey thru life's hardships.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
more specifically for me, and for anyone else who believes in heaven, it is a reminder that the true "infinity" is one day all pain and suffering in this world will be done. a reminder that pain and injustice won't have the final word.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
and also the reminder that we aren't there yet, and therefore i want to do all i can to help others during this time where so much pain and injustice exists in this world.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
everything i am doing with restoring heart is sprung from that desire to help people - whatever their hardship. to help you move forward in the midst of fear - one brave baby step at a time, like i did.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
facing what happened to me and working through it was the most difficult thing of my entire life, but eventually, i reached a point where i no longer felt imprisoned by what happened to me.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
also, by fighting for myself, i learned to truly love and value myself.  and i want that same thing for you!⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i hope each week's episode of the restoring heart podcast is helping you wherever you find yourself in life.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
for #metoo survivors, i look forward to opening haven in late january. it will be an online space with videos and a community with other survivors for you to walk alongside with. stay tuned. <3⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
#sexualabuse #survivor #sexualtrauma #sexualassault #healing #tattoo

text:
we've been talking about sexual harassment, and so we had to bring in some statistics. 🚫
this image is from a study conducted by the university of texas.  approximately 20 percent of female science students and 25 percent of female engineering students (undergraduate and graduate), said they had been sexually harassed by faculty or staff. 
but among medical students - woah- 47 percent of women in medical school said they’d been sexually harassed by faculty or staff.
🚫
other survey's have shown medical students to have rates as high as 50% reporting sexual harassment. 🚫
this is not acceptable.  #asawoman, we should be welcomed into medicine.  as dr. chernoby so eloquently put it.  as women, sexual harassment should not be the price of admission into the house of medicine.
🚫
image from https://www.statnews.com/2018/06/12/sexual-harassment-science-nasem-report/

text:
猪股です。instagramではお久しぶりです。

今回は、政治の村studentsのお知らせです。地域魅惑内のプロジェクトでもあり、タウンニュース社が運営する学生の言論サイト「政治のむらstudents 」では、この度2018年回顧をテーマに3つの記事を更新しました。

1つは私、猪股の記事です。今年の漢字「災」から防災について考えた「『防災』という作法」を執筆致しました。災害が相次ぐ中、防災にも目を向けたいところです。

2つ目は武蔵大学4年の漢人さんが執筆した「地域の社会と消費 守れ商店街」。インターネットの商業が台頭する中、地元商店街が何に力を取り組んでいるのか。漢人さんの住まいは、今年百貨店の撤退があった船橋。地元のことを織り交ぜつつ、漢人さんの論点が掲載されています。

3つ目は東海大3年の澤村さんが執筆した「性暴力と闘う」。2018年に注目を浴びたmetoo運動について澤村さんの論考が掲載されています。澤村さんは今年、性教育をテーマにしたフリーペーパーを企画・発行しました。精力的に活動する澤村さんだからこそ書ける、鋭い指摘は、より多くの方の目に留まって欲しいです。

記事は以下のurlから閲覧できます！ぜひ、ご覧ください！そして皆さん、良いお年を！ 【性暴力と闘う】
https://seijinomura.townnews.co.jp/students/2018/12/post.html 【地域の社会と消費　守れ商店街】
https://seijinomura.townnews.co.jp/students/2018/12/24.html 【「防災」という作法】
https://seijinomura.townnews.co.jp/students/2018/12/10.html

1つは私、猪股の記事です。今年の漢字「災」から防災について考えた「『防災』という作法」を執筆致しました。災害が相次ぐ中、防災にも目を向けたいところです。

2つ目は武蔵大学4年の漢人さんが執筆した「地域の社会と消費 守れ商店街」。インターネットの商業が台頭する中、地元商店街が何に力を取り組んでいるのか。漢人さんの住まいは、今年百貨店の撤退があった船橋。地元のことを織り交ぜつつ、漢人さんの論点が掲載されています。

3つ目は東海大3年の澤村さんが執筆した「性暴力と闘う」。2018年に注目を浴びたmetoo運動について澤村さんの論考が掲載されています。澤村さんは今年、性教育をテーマにしたフリーペーパーを企画・発行しました。精力的に活動する澤村さんだからこそ書ける、鋭い指摘は、より多くの方の目に留まって欲しいです。

記事は以下のurlから閲覧できます！ぜひ、ご覧ください！そして皆さん、良いお年を！ 【性暴力と闘う】

https://seijinomura.townnews.co.jp/students/2018/12/24.html 【「防災」という作法】
https://seijinomura.townnews.co.jp/students/2018/12/10.html

text: standing up for what you believe in will create positive change in the world! it is not always comfortable and sometimes it may get you in trouble, but advocating for what you think is right will create a more just and equal world. i have been a fighter my whole life and it’s definitely put me in some difficult situations, but i would rather use my power and privilege to make changes for the greater good than sit back and watch the faces of oppression eat away at our vulnerable populations. cultural change requires plenty of small actions by large groups of people and being an activist does not have to be your full time job!

text:
kochi-muziris biennale 2018
a personal selection 
1. photographies by juul kraijer
2. con-struction i, by arunkumar hg
3. for, in your tongue, i cannot fit : 100 jailed poets, by shilpa gupta
4. a spoken poem in a bottle, by shilpa gupta
5. ocha, by vinu vv
6. guerilla girls
7. water temple, by song dong
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
this edition of the kochi biennale is entitled « possibilities for a non-alienated life » and wonderfully well curated by indian artist anita dube. politically charged and profoundly disruptive, this biennale is placed under the hashtags #metoo and #lgbtqrights , in hopes of a dialogue for a better world.
the biennale ends on march 29th 2019, so come quick! kerala is a wonderful place to visit (see next post) and it’s nice and warm in the winter! ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
an excerpt of anita dube’s curatorial note:
« i remember guy debord’s warnings of a world mediated primarily through images— a society of the spectacle —as i write this note. that such a society is fascism’s main ally, we are all discovering in different parts of the world today.
virtual hyper-connectivity has paradoxically alienated us from the warm solidarities of community— that place of embrace where we can enjoy our intelligence and beauty with others, where we can love —a place where we don’t need the ‘other’ as an enemy to feel connected ».
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
#kochimuzirisbiennale #biennale2018 #kerala #india #contemporaryart #anitadube #juulkraijer #arunkumarhg #shilpagupta #vinuvv #guerillagirls #songdong #feminism #artforall
